Commentary.Commentary: 19 overs left in the day. Around an hour to go. The Aussie bowlers will be hoping to rest their feet in the dressing room for a day at least. How many wickets can England get before Stumps? They can have one of the Aussie bowlers in as a night watchman then. Stay tuned for the Aussie reply.

The hosts were in trouble at 138/6 when Bairstow and Woakes joined forces. Their 72-run stand gave some respectability to the total and got the score beyond 200. After Woakes fell, Jonny marshalled the tail to get the score past 250.

England will be happy with the momentum, but not with the score. If truth be told, they only had difficulty in playing out the first hour where they lost Roy and Root. But after that, their batsmen got starts but could not convert. The likes of Burns, Denly, Buttler and Stokes, all got their eye in but could not make a big impact.

However, let us focus on Tim Paine and Australia. After winning the toss and electing to bowl, if you can bowl the opposition out for around 250, you have done a decent job. The spotlight was on the comeback man, Josh Hazlewood, who sparkled with his 3 wickets. Nathan Lyon took care of the middle order while Cummins got 3 as well. A really good bowling performance where it was not a one-man show.
The Lord's gets up as one to applaud Jonny Bairstow off the park. From 138/6, to almost double the score is a really good effort. The batting line-up which is touted to be strong, did show its depth.

OUT! In the air... taken! End of the England innings! Bairstow is the last man to fall and Lyon is the one who takes the last wicket. This is floated up on middle, Bairstow looks to play the slog sweep. He tries to take on the bowler but only manages a top edge towards deep mid-wicket. Khawaja in the deep runs ahead and takes it nicely. ENGLAND HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 258!

FOUR! Handy runs for England here as Leach dispatches this for a boundary. This one is on the body of Leach, little bit down the leg side. He just nudges it fine, wide of the keeper and the ball crashes into the fine leg fence.
Play and a miss! Hazlewood bowls this one on middle and the ball goes away from Leach with the angle. Leach tries to play at it but fails as he does so inside the line of the delivery.
Bairstow plays this good length ball towards deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
On the body of Bairstow, he awkwardly keeps it down on the leg side as the ball takes the inside edge of the bat.
Full ball again on middle and off, Bairstow plays it towards silly mid on where Warner is placed.
Fullish ball just outside the off pole, Bairstow plays it towards mid on.
Josh Hazlewood is back into the attack. He has been the best bowler for Australia today. Can he get the last wicket now?
Fuller and on middle, Leach hits it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air on middle, this is defended onto the ground.
On the pads, Leach works it through square leg and takes two.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On the stumps again, Leach is solid in defense again.
On middle, Leach lunges and keeps it out.

A loud LBW appeal by Australia but turned down by Aleem Dar. Good length ball around middle and leg. Bairstow tries to flick it but misses to get hit on the pads. A loud appeal follows but the umpire shakes his head. The Hawk Eye comes in and shows and confirms that the umpire got his decision spot on as the ball was going down the leg pole.
Powerful punch this time towards covers to this full ball outside off. The fielder there gathers it. No runs taken.
Fullish ball on off, Bairstow plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller ball on off, Bairstow blocks it out towards mid off.
Length ball just outside off, Bairstow again leaves it. He should be looking to score some runs here as this is the last wicket.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
OHHH! This is flatter and on off, it turns away after pitching. Leach looks to defend but is beaten by the away turn.
Jack Leach is the last man in for England. The last time he batted for England he scored 92. England would be happy if he can get even half of those right now.

OUT! TIMBER! No. 9 goes down! Lyon gets his second. This is the arm ball on off and it keeps coming in with the angle. Broad looks to defend but does so outside the line. It goes off the inside edge and kiss the leg pole. Another handy stand for England comes to an end.
Flatter and on off, Broad guides it to point.
FOUR! Broad gets into the position of playing a paddle sweep early. Lyon looks to fire it but ends up bowling a full toss. Broad uses the pace and hits it to the fine leg fence. 250 up for England.
Swept and swept hard but just for a single towards deep square leg.
Floats it up on middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
A bumper to end! Broad ducks under it.
Good fielding! Saves two for his side. Shorter and on middle, Cummins this plays a controlled pull shot through square leg. The fielder in the deep, Wade, runs to his left, dives and stops it.
FOUR BYES! Way down the leg side by Cummins. Broad looks to tuck but misses. Paine dives to his right but he has no chance. It races to the fine leg fence.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Length ball on the off side this by Cummins, Broad tries to play it towards fine leg but gets a top edge on it. The ball goes over the slip cordon towards third man loopily. David Warner gives it a chase, dives forward, gets two hands to it but can not collect it properly. He will be disappointed that he couldn't catch that and Broad survives this time.

Fifty for Bairstow! He has played well to get his team to a competitive total on this surface but he will be looking to carry on. This is full and outside off, Bairstow powerfully pushes it towards deep extra cover and takes a single to complete his half ton.
Good length and outside off, this is left alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Lyon trying to induce the drive but Broad is not interested as he lets it be.
Floated and wide outside off, Broad lets it be.
This time also full and on the off side, Broad pushes it back towards mid off.
Again wide outside off, Broad does not fiddle with it.
Floated and wide outside off, Broad lets it be.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Dismissed! Slightly short and on middle, JB picks the length early and smashes it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Broad gets off the mark as he plays this length ball towards point.
Good length ball on the legs to start off for Broad. He manages to keep it down and not give a chance to the short leg fielder.
Stuart Broad is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Great catch by Khawaja running back from gully! Cummins gets another one on a short ball. He bowls this one on the body. Archer looks to nudge it on the leg side. He closes the face of the bat early. A leading edge is induced and the ball balloons over Khawaja who runs back and takes a very good diving catch. Australia two wickets away from ending the England innings.
Good length  ball on the off pole line, Bairstow gets on the front foot and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Full and flat on off, Archer pushes it back towards mid off.
Again on the leg side, Bairstow paddles it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Flat and on the hips of JB, he blocks it on the leg side.
Flat and wide outside off, Bairstow sweeps it towards deep square leg and takes two as the fielders in the deep cut it off.
On middle, Archer uses his wrists and guides it towards long on for a single.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
Nathan Lyon returns. 15-1-57-1 so far.
Length ball on middle and off, Bairstow defends it off the back foot.
Well maneuvered by Archer here. Good length ball on his hips, he flicks it uppishly over short leg and takes a single.
Third bouncer of the over, Cummins bowls this one again on the leg pole line.
FOUR! Gift gladly accepted by Archer. Full on the pads of Archer, he just gets a nick on it and the ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Another shorter one on the leg pole line, Archer keeps his eyes in the ball and ducks under it.
Shorter one by Cummins to Archer on the leg side, he ducks under it and lets it through to the keeper.
Good batting! Archer pushes this good length ball towards the cover region and takes one.
On a good length and around off, Archer guides it to point.
FOUR! Poor ball! Short and outside off, Archer stands tall and cuts it over point for a boundary.
Good length and outside off, shaping away further. Archer hangs his bat out but gets beaten.
Fuller and attacking the stumps this time, Archer blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Archer lets it be.
On off, Bairstow plays it late towards the slip cordon. Second slip makes a good stop.
In the air... but too quick for short leg to react. This is shorter and on the body, Archer works it uppishly but it goes past short leg quickly and through square leg for one.
Change of length this time, Archer does well to keep this good length ball down as Bancroft is standing at short leg to take the catch.
This is the third bouncer of the over. Umpire Aleem Dar signals the one bouncer warning. Archer tries to hook but misses the ball as it carries to the keeper.
Another bumper, Archer once again ducks under it.
A good short one to welcome the debutant. He ducks under it.
Hazlewood goes for the bouncer, Bairstow ducks under it and lets it through to the keeper.
Fullish and on off, driven towards covers by Bairstow.
Good length ball on the off pole, Bairstow gets an inside edge onto the pads as the ball rolls towards cover-point.
Full again but this time on middle, Bairstow pushes it towards mid on.
Full ball just outside the off pole, Bairstow drives this towards the covers. The man there dives to his left and makes a brilliant stop.
FOUR! Deft! Shorter and just outside off, Bairstow waits for it and the guides it through backward point for a boundary. He is playing really well out there. Into the 40s now.
Jofra Archer is the new man in.

OUT! There is spike on Ultra Edge and Woakes has to walk back. He takes a review along with him. Not sure why he reviewed, you would always know if you have got something on the ball as a batter. End of a good stand for England though. Australia will be delighted as they have broken the 72-run stand. Another short one, Woakes is just not comfortable with these kind of deliveries. This is on the body. Woakes shuffles across and looks to pull but it goes off the glove and straight to Paine who takes it and appeals. The finger goes up. Woakes feels he hasn't touched it and goes upstairs. Replays roll in and they show that there is glove involved.

Caught behind! Or is he? Woakes has been adjudged caught down the leg side by umpire Aleem Dar. Woakes though, says he is not sure and takes the review. Here comes Ultra Edge. A spike when the ball passes the glove. End of the 72-run stand.

In the air... but safe! Cummins goes short again and on the body. Woakes takes his eyes off the ball and then tries to pull. He is early in the pull. It goes off the toe-end up in the air but well short of mid on. He is really not comfortable with the short balls at the moment.
The physio is out to have a look. Woakes is taking his time and rightly so. The concussion test is being held and also a few other helmets are begin brought. The good thing is though, he seems fine.

Right on the temple! That must have really hurt Woakes. He seems really shook at the moment. A short one on middle, this one does not bounce a lot. Woakes looks to duck but is hit straight on the helmet. He takes a few seconds to get back to his feet. Cummins and the close-in Australian fielders straightaway walk towards him to see whether he is fine.
Down the leg side this time by Cummins, Woakes tries to flick but misses.
SIX! Cummins again goes for the shorter one. Woakes looks to pull but top edges it and the ball flies over the fine leg fence for a biggie. Woakes had no idea where this one went.

Sarvesh - 'England were 201 in 61 overs. Have they scored only 3 runs in 3 overs?' @Sarvesh - Well, one can understand your impatience but the session has just begun. Another 15 minutes of watchfulness and we might see some leather hunting.
Another bumper but this time much lower, near head height. Woakes goes for the hook but misses. Probably getting a tad bit frustrated.
Wide! Bouncer, but way too high over the head of Woakes.
Fuller this time to Bairstow, he just drives it powerfully down the ground. It hits the stumps at the bowler's end and then the legs of the umpire. No runs taken.
Finally Hazlewood attacks the stumps, Woakes swivels towards the off side and plays it towards mid-wicket to take a single.
Woakes is patiently waiting for the bad delivery. He again leaves this ball which is way outside off.
Similar line this time too, Woakes again lets it be.
This one moves away after pitching, Woakes does not fiddle with it.
Close to the stumps, good length ball just outside off. Woakes knows exactly where his stumps are and he lets it through to the keeper.
Outside off on a length, Bairstow lets it through to the keeper.
Fuller this time outside the off pole, Bairstow drives it towards mid off powerfully. It goes straight towards the fielder standing there.
Outside off, Bairstow lets it be.
Bouncer! Cummins hits this one hard on the deck, the ball rises near Bairstow's head. He ducks under it and the ball goes to the keeper.
This time just outside off, Jonny plays it towards the short cover fielder.
Good length ball on the middle pole by Cummins, JB blocks it out.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end. He has a wicket to his name in  his 14 overs. Australia would love one more here.
Good ball to finish off the over. Good length ball just outside off, Woakes tries to defend at it but misses as he plays inside the line. Good start after the break for Australia.
Length ball just outside off, Woakes lets it be.
First run after the break. This is on a good length on middle, Jonny dabs it towards the leg side and takes a single.
Yorker just outside off, Jonny jams it out towards the point region.
Fuller and on middle, pushed towards mid on by JB.
Good length on the off pole to start with. Bairstow blocks it out towards the off side.

The Australian players walk out for the final time today! They are followed by the English batters, Jonny Bairstow and Chris Woakes. 37 overs left in the day so we are in for another long session. Jonny Bairstow will take strike and he will be facing Josh Hazlewood. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

Australia on the other hand, can be pleased with how they bowled. All the four bowlers picked a wicket in this session. However, since it was a longer session, it did seem like they were tiring towards the end and hence, run scoring got a little easy for the current English pair. They now though will get a little rest and hope to come out after the break and bundle England out as quickly as possible. Will they be able to do so? We will have to wait a while to find out.

This session - 34 overs, 125 runs, 4 wickets and a run rate of close to 4. End of a long but a very good session of Test cricket! Another one which in the end can be said will be shared. However, one can argue, Australia at the moment do hold the edge. They had the perfect start to this session as they got rid of Denly early. Then Burns followed. Buttler and Stokes did not last for long too. Just as it seemed another English collapse is on the cards, Woakes and Bairstow stepped up. The two played positively and have now taken England to safer shores. They have added 63 and are not yet done. England will hope the two keep going.
One more single as another delivery is worked through square leg for one. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Now from over the wicket, he lands it on off, the ball turns back in. Woakes goes back, lets the ball do its bit and then works it towards square leg for one. 200 up for England.
On middle, Jonny works it through square leg and takes one.
Lands it on middle again, Bairstow works it with the turn to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked to the man at short leg.
Flatter and on off, JB goes back and keeps it out.

Edged and away! Smith bowls it very full on middle, Woakes looks to drive it down the ground but it turns away. It goes off the outside edge but wide of the first slip fielder and down towards third man for two.
This is on the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. One run added to the total.
Flatter and on middle, CW goes back and defends it onto the ground.
Loopy ball on off, this is hit to the man at mid off.
Floats it up on off, Bairstow looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through the leg side for one.
Around off, Woakes lunges and pushes it to covers.
Down the leg side and Woakes does not play at it.
On middle again, Bairstow flicks it through mid-wicket and takes another single.
Gives it a lot of air on middle, Woakes works it through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on off, Woakes goes back and defends it onto the ground.
Tosses it up on middle, Woakes defends it.
Way outside off this time by Smith, Bairstow looks to play at it but misses.

NOT OUT! Looked like it was always going to miss the off pole and it does as the Hawk Eye confirms. Smith floats this one outside off, the ball pitches and straightens. Bairstow offers the leave and it hits his pad along the way to the keeper. Smith is not entirely convinced but Paine still takes the review and it is lost as the ball is missing the off pole by a big margin. Australia have lost both their reviews now and they will be hoping they do not live to regret it.
Australia review as an appeal for an LBW has been turned down. Looks to be missing off. It seems like a waste of a review.
Again full and around middle, it hits the inside edge of Bairstow's blade and onto the pads.
Fuller this time around off, Bairstow pushes this towards mid off.
Shorter this time, Bairstow punches it off the back foot towards the off side.
Short of a length ball outside off, Woakes pushes it to deep point and takes a single.
Steve Smith is into the attack now. He is being booed by the fans here. However, that is the reception he has been receiving throughout the series till now. He has responded in great fashion though.
On the pads, Bairstow pads it away. Lyon makes a huge appeal but not sure why. 10 from the over, a very good one for England.
Loopy ball on the pads, JB works it towards backward square leg and takes two.

FOUR! 50-run stand is up! Bairstow brings it up by playing a lovely shot. He brings out the reverse sweep and hits it nicely behind point for a boundary. A vital stand this, they are slowly but steadily taking England to safer shores.
FOUR! Nice shot! This was against the turn but Bairstow played it really well. This is tossed up outside off, JB leans into it and strokes it through covers for a boundary. Partnership is now 46.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Floats it up on off, it is kept out.

Play and a miss again. Hazlewood looking menacing here. Again full and just outside off, the ball moves away after pitching. Woakes tries to defend but does so inside the line. The wicket might just be around the corner.
Wide outside off stump, Woakes lets it be.
Length ball again and on off, Woakes gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it out.
Length ball down the leg side, Woakes tries to flick but misses.

Edged and short! Woakes living dangerously here. Again fuller and around off, this time Woakes does get an outside edge on it. However, the ball falls short of Warner at first slip. Maybe the slip cordon should take a few steps forward.
Play and a miss! Fuller and just outside off, Woakes goes to drive but misses it as he is late into the shot. Maybe he is too worried about the short ball in the back of his mind.
On middle, Woakes works it with the turn through square leg for one.
Flatter and outside off, JB guides it towards point and gets to the other end.
On the leg stump and then spinning away. Bairstow looks to flick but misses.
On middle, Bairstow works it to short leg.
FOUR! Not off the middle but England won't care. This is floated around off, Bairstow looks to play the sweep shot this time, it goes off the inner half fine on the leg side for a boundary.
Nicely played! Brings the paddle sweep out and hits it towards fine leg for two.
Change of ends for Nathan Lyon.

FOUR! Good shot by Woakes this. A little unorthodox but gets the desired result. Hazlewood bowls this one short and on middle, Woakes gets up on one leg and plays a short arm jab towards mid-wicket for a boundary.  Travis Head gives it a good chase from deep square leg and dives but cannot get there.

Great fielding! Wade flies to his right and saves at least a run for his side. Good length ball on the off side by Hazlewood, Woakes pushes hard at it. The ball goes wide of the man at cover, Matthew Wade but he dives to his right and fields superbly. Gets pats on the back from his teammates as well.
Length ball just outside off, Woakes blocks this one out towards cover-point.
Selfie Lad - 'Hey commentator. Like minds think alike. I was just about to ask when is this never-ending session going to end and you just posted an update. Thanks!' @Selfie - Telepathy.
Full ball on off, Woakes pushes it out towards mid off.
Good length ball again but this time on the pads, Jonny tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Good length ball just outside off, JB lets it through to the keeper.
Normally, we would have had Tea by now, but because we lost an entire day due to rain yesterday, Tea has been extended by half an hour. It will be taken at 4.10 pm local (1510 GMT).
Slightly fuller and outside off, the batter shoulders arms to this one.
Shorter in length and on middle, Bairstow pulls it towards deep backward square leg for one.
This is angled into the batter, the line is a little too straight. Jonny looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Good length and just outside off, it has been left alone.
Good shot but for no runs! Fuller and on off, JB strokes it towards mid off where the fielder moves to his right and stops it nicely.
This is angled on the pads, it is worked towards deep backward square leg for one.

Hazlewood induces the outside edge again but this time from Woakes. He again pitches it on a length outside off, Woakes pushes at it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes away from the slip cordon and towards third man as the batters are able to take three runs.
Fuller this time and on the pads, Bairstow pushes it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

Edged but short! Hazlewood bowls this one just outside off, it nips away after pitching. Bairstow plays at it with soft hands and thus the ball falls just short of first slip where Warner was placed. Bairstow survives.
Full ball on off, good shot by Bairstow towards cover-point but Khawaja dives to his left and saves at least a couple of runs for his side.
Again similar line and length, Bairstow lets it go.
Nice start again by Hazlewood, he is getting some zip off the pitch. The ball is pitched on a length just outside off and rises. Bairstow lets it through and Paine collects it near chest height.
Josh Hazlewood is back on!
A dot to end! This is on off, Woakes defends it onto the ground.
Wide of the crease goes Siddle this time and bowls it outside off, it has been left alone.
Good length and on off, Woakes is once again solid in defense.
Almost plays it on! Back of a length on off, Woakes looks to defend but does so quite late. It goes off the inside edge and it bounces ahead of the stumps and then goes past them.
Good length and on off, Woakes stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
A little too straight, Bairstow works it through square leg and takes one.
Lyon bowls this one fullish and on middle and off, it hits Woakes on the pads. Good over by Lyon comes to an end.
This time fuller and on middle, Woakes again defends it.
Loopy and on off, Woakes blocks it out.
FOUR! Full ball wide outside off, Woakes comes on the front foot and pushes it through covers for a beautiful boundary.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

Loud appeal from the Aussies for an LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Lyon loops this one on off pole and the ball spins in and hits the pad of Woakes. He tries to flick it towards the leg side but misses. Woakes has put in a big stride forward and thus, the ball might have turned too much to hit the stumps. The Hawk Eye comes in and proves it as the ball is missing the leg pole. Good decision by the umpire here.
A length ball to end but it is outside off, left alone.
The 5th ball is angled into the pads, Woakes works it down to fine leg for one.
Another ball on a length and outside off, Woakes does not play at it.
On a good length and outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR LEG BYES! On the pads, Woakes looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The bowler is appealing but the umpire shakes his head. The ball in the meantime goes to the fine leg fence.
JB comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of the ball. He tries to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On off, Bairstow goes back and pushes it to covers.
Shorter and outside off, Woakes cuts it through point for one.
This one stays low! Flatter and on off, Woakes gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
FOUR! Good shot! Good use of the feet by Woakes. 150 up for England. He steps down the track and with the turn works it through mid-wicket. It races away to the fence.
Loopy ball on off, Woakes looks to defend but the ball turns back in and goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! JB replies perfectly to Siddle. A hint fuller on off by Siddle this time, Bairstow just leans into the drive and pushes it through mid off for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, JB lets it through to the keeper.
Beaten! Beauty by Siddle! He pitches this on a good length on the fourth stump line. It pitches and nips away from Jonny who defends inside the line of the delivery. Oohs and Aahs by the Aussies.
Full and outside off, Bairstow guides it towards covers.
Good length ball this time just outside off, played back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Good length ball on the off pole and it is pummeled down the ground by Bairstow through mid on.

An appeal for a stumping has been taken upstairs! Australia do not seem excited. NOT OUT! Woakes has his feet in. The arm ball outside off, Woakes lunges and defends for the turn. The ball goes straight on and past the outside edge. Paine collects the ball and whips the bails off. Replays show that Woakes is in. End of a brilliant over by Lyon.
Flatter and outside off, this turns back in. Woakes goes back and looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Floats it up on off, Woakes lunges and keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, this is defended.
Chris Woakes is the next man in.

OUT! LBW! Lyon gets Stokes again! England in deep trouble now. Unlucky 13 strikes for Stokes. He looks to sweep this ball on the stumps. Misses and gets hit on the front pad. An appeal and the umpire raises the finger. Stokes thinks about the review, asks his partner but does not get the nod. He stands up, turns and starts walking back. Into the bowling all-rounders now are Australia. Here comes the Hawk Eye and it shows three reds.
Flatter and outside off, this is left alone.
On a good length and around off, it is kept out.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
On a good length and outside off, left alone.
Unplayable! Not a lot you can do there. This starts on off and then shapes away. Bairstow defends the original trajectory but gets beaten.
Fuller and around off, Bairstow drives it to point.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Bairstow plays inside the line and lets it be.
Loopy ball outside off, it once again pitches and turns. Stokes looks to defend but is beaten again. End of a very good over by Lyon.
On the stumps this time, Stokes defends it onto the ground.

Almost a replica of the way Stokes was dismissed in the 4th innings of the first Test. This is tossed up outside off, it pitches and turns away. Stokes lunges and tries to defend but the ball turns away and beats the outside edge.
Slower through the air outside off, the batsman lets it be.
Shorter and outside off, Stokes cuts it to point.
On the pads, it is worked towards fine leg for one.
Bairstow is off the mark! On middle, Bairstow looks to play it with a straight bat but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one. A successful over from Siddle comes to an end.
Way too wide outside off, left alone.

That is a jaffa! Almost two in two for Siddle. He goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Bairstow is not sure whether to play at it or not to. In the end he bails out. The ball goes just over the off pole. A nervous start by JB.
Jonny Bairstow walks in at number 7, replacing Buttler.

OUT! Caught behind! Stop the press. Siddle has got a wicket. Yes, stop printing! At last, he gets some luck and the bowling change works for Paine. It is a very good delivery, landing on a length just outside off and forcing Buttler to play at that. He does so but the late movement does him in. It is not too much but just enough to take the outside edge. Simple catch for Tim Paine and England are now 5 down.
Interesting. Jos walks into this shot and pushes the ball to cover. Normally, batsmen adopt this technique either to cover the swing or if there is no swing.
Full and outside off, a touch wider to be enticed, Buttler lets it be.
Peter Siddle returns. 7-1-35-0 so far.
FOUR! STUPENDOUS! Nothing edgy or flashy or lucky about this stroke. Full and around off, Stokes gets down and mows a sweep, powerfully through mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGED, FOUR! How close was that? Very close. Flashed down to third man. Outside off, Stokes goes back but does not actually play any shot. He waits and waits and waits and at the last possible moment, slashes hard. That perhaps confuses both Paine and Smith at first slip. They react late when the edge is induced and the ball flies low beneath Steve's left hand and escapes to the third man fence.
Very full, slowly looped, around middle, pushed back.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, spinning away, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Pacy delivery, outside off, solidly defended.
Field change. Someone is going back to the square leg boundary.
A bouncer, outside off, calmly ducked under.
On a length around off, Stokes gets on top of the bounce and punches it in the gap between cover and point for a single. Good spell this from Cummins so far. 6.4 overs, 1/16.
A bit of inward movement this time, JB covers it nicely and works it through fine leg for a single.
Outside off, on a length, moving away, Jos looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge, on the bounce, to second slip.
Down the leg side, Buttler looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. The ball goes off those towards the keeper.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Fired down the leg side, BS gets back to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. A mild LBW appeal ensues but it is in vain. Going down leg.
Goes right back in his crease and defends once again.
Full and outside off, Ben gets right behind the line and blocks.
Around middle and off, watchfully defended.
Full and around off, Buttler drives it off the inner half of the bat past the bowler towards mid on for a single.
Nathan Lyon is back!
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Hammered away! Off the mark in style! Short and on middle, Stokes is ready for it. He pulls it hard through mid-wicket and the ball races away to the fence.
FIVE WIDES! This is way too short and on middle, Stokes lets it be. It goes over the keeper and into the third man fence.
A good short one again, Stokes ducks under it.
Ben Stokes walks out to replace Rory Burns in the middle.

OUT! That is clean as a whistle! Take a bow, Bancroft. You have taken an absolute blinder. Unbelievable. Rory Burns' luck runs out. The ploy to bowl short has worked. Cummins bowls another one on his body. Burns stands tall and looks to nudge it on the leg side. It goes to the left of short leg where CB dives to his left and seems to have taken it. The Aussies are celebrating but Burns holds his ground. The umpire takes it upstairs. Soft signal is OUT! Replays roll in and they show that the ball did pop out but Bancroft keeps his eyes on the ball and takes it on the second attempt. A good innings by Burns comes to an end but now Australia have both the set batters back in the hut. They are right back in this now.
Has that been taken? If it is, it is a stunner. Burns is the man in question. The umpires take it upstairs. SOFT SIGNAL IS OUT!
Nasty stuff! Shorter around off and angling away. Burns looks to defend it by hopping but the ball whizzes past the outside edge. Testing times for Burns.
A short one on the leg side, ducked under.

FOUR! Through covers again! Maybe, Siddle should have a cover fielder in place. That is how he is bowling too. Full and outside off, Buttler leans into it and creams it through covers for a boundary. Siddle has been very expensive today.

Well bowled! He kept taking the ball away and this time angles it into the batter. Buttler looks to flick it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat early. A soft leading edge to point is induced.
Another one outside off, it is left alone.
A lot of away swing for the bowler there but it is way too outside off. Left alone.
Fuller and on off, JB hits it to mid off.
On the fuller side outside off, Buttler lets it be.
A couple! Shorter and on the body, Burns nudges it down to fine leg and takes two. A testing over by Cummins comes to an end.
That has hit Burns again! Slightly short again, this time too Burns fails to get out of the way and is hit on the body.
Another short one! This time Burns was ready for it as he ducks under it.
OUCH! That might have hurt. Shorter and on the body, Burns does not have enough time to move out of the way and gets hit on the shoulder.
Shorter and on the body, Burns looks to nudge it around the corner but it hits the higher part of the bat and goes down onto the pitch.
This is on off, it is angled into the batter, Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the inner half down to fine leg for one.

Fifty for Burns! This is what happens when you give a good player not one but two chances. He will surely make you pay. This is on off and on a length. Burns pushes it through covers and takes two. Will he score another ton here?
Another back of a length ball on off, this is defended.
He moves onto 49! Shorter and outside off, Burns pushes it through covers for two.
Good length and on off, it is defended.
On middle, Burns keeps it out.

DROPPED! Peter Siddle has just not had the luck he needs! Once again a catch has been dropped off his bowling. Burns, just like the first Test, continues riding his luck. The skipper is the culprit this time. Siddle bowls it fuller and around off, it shapes away. Burns goes after it away from the body. It goes off the outside edge to the left and low of Paine. He dives and goes for it with one hand but fails to hang on. Maybe he felt it would not have carried so Paine did not give his 100 percent. Just did not seem right as he was going down there. Never looked like taking it.
Peter Siddle is on now.

Selfie lad - 'What is with Burns and Lady Luck? In the last match, Australia did not review an LBW decision against him in the first innings facing Nathan Lyon and here, Usman Khawaja dropped a dolly. And he keeps scoring and scoring and scoring...' @Selfie - Hmmm.... fair point. That too, both chances came pretty early in the innings. At Edgbaston, Rory was on 19 and here, on 11. So the key is - get Rory early, else, he will BURN you.
On the off pole again, Buttler defends it out solidly.
A short one on middle, Jos ducks under it.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed towards mid off.
Lovely delivery! This is slightly fuller and around off, Buttler looks to defend but the ball straightens and it beats the outside edge.
Attacks the off pole, Jos defends it.
Back of a length on off, Buttler guides it to point.

FOUR! Hazlewood goes for runs for the first time in this match. This is outside off and on a length, Burns opens the face of the bat and guides it towards the third man fence for a boundary. 13 runs off the over. England are 105/3.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

FOUR BYES! Also brings up 100 runs for England. The ball is pitched wide outside the leg side, it pitches and swings further away. Burns tries to flick it away but misses. Paine behind does get a hand to it but fails to stop it. The ball goes to the fine leg fence and a boundary results.
Length ball on the off side, Burns plays it towards mid off.
Good bouncer by Hazlewood again. Pitching on middle and leg, the ball rises after pitching. Burns ducks under it and lets it through to the keeper.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! Bonus runs for England! This is on off, Buttler drops it towards point and takes off. Lyon picks the ball up and has a shy at the non-striker's end but the ball flicks the pad of Buttler and goes away from the fielder backing up and to the mid-wicket fence. Buttler has five from the first ball he faces.
Well bowled and well played! Good cricket all around. A short one just outside off, Burns at the very end evades it.
Another one on the shorter side, Burns rises on his toes and keeps it out.
Back of a length again on middle, RB defends it onto the ground.
Shorter and outside off, Burns lets it be.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Good length and on off, Burns guides it to point.
Jos Buttler is the new man in.

OUT! Caught behind! Hazlewood is the breakthrough provider once again. Lovely, lovely delivery. Hazlewood lands it on a length and around off, it shapes away late. Denly does not adjust to the movement as he defends inside the line. The ball kisses the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper. A much-needed wicket for the visitors as this partnership was really going nicely. End of the 66-run stand though. Early wicket for Australia after the break. Also, replays show later on that Denly did not have a good stride forward, maybe he was worried about the short ball which he was quite uncomfortable against.
This time it is on a length, Denly keeps it out. We would see more of length from Hazlewood and one surprise short one.
Short to Denly now and Joe ducks under it. Maybe they have a plan is to bowl short for a while now.
Loose stroke! Shorter and outside off, Denly goes after it away from the body but misses.
On middle, Denly works it to wide mid on.

Yes, no, yes and then a single in the end! This is around off, Burns guides it towards point and takes a few steps down the track. The fielder at point makes a half-stop. Denly goes for the run then. Burns is ball-watching but spots his partner coming towards him and then goes for it as well. They complete it.

FOUR BYES! Too high this time by Cummins. He goes for another bouncer but pitches it too short. It goes way over the head of Denly. He does not fend at it and the ball goes over Tim Paine's head too although he leaps and does get a glove on it. It doesn't make any difference as the ball goes towards the fine leg fence.

Unusual bounce on this one. The ball pitches on middle, short of a length. It rockets off the pitch and rapidly goes towards Denly. He tries to evade it but gets hit hard on his left bicep. He looks okay though. Probably he should wear an arm guard against bowler's who consistently bowl about 140 kph.
Bumper once again, Denly is not worried as it is too high.
Length ball outside off, played to point off the back foot.

This length ball pitches on middle and rises, it hits the handle of Denly's bat and falls towards short leg. He gets one hand off the bat as he tries to play at it and thus the ball doesn't go far away from him.
Full ball just outside the off pole, Denly blocks it.
Again full and on middle, Burns blocks it out. Maiden for Josh in his second over after the break.
Fuller and on off, RB plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller this time on the legs of Burns, he tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Good bumper by Hazlewood! It is bowled on middle and leg, Burns quickly ducks under it.
Fullish ball just outside the off pole, Burns defends it back towards the bowler.
Short of a length ball on leg, Burns looks to flick it but he gets hit on the thigh pad as the ball rolls towards the off side.
A dot to end! On off, Denly stands tall and keeps it out.

A loud shout but once again the umpire shakes his head. Too high? Paine does signal that. This is around off and it jags back in. Denly looks to drive but misses to get hit high on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down. Hawk Eye shows it to be clipping the top of the stumps. Australia need to get it a little more fuller than the length they are bowling.
On a length this time around off, Denly is solid in defense.
Back of a length on off, Denly stands tall and keeps it out.
Slightly shorter and just outside off, left alone.
Another one which is angled into the batter, Denly works it through square leg and takes two.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end.
Another dot! Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off. 9 from the first over after resumption.
Good length and on off, this is defended onto the ground. A DOT!
Another two! All four balls after the break have been scored off. This is on the pads, Burns works it down towards fine leg. The fielder there runs to his left, dives and saves two for his side.
Runs again! This is outside off, Burns plays it with an angled bat down towards third man for two.
FOUR! Nice way to start the session for Burns. This is shorter and outside off, Rory stands tall and pushes it through covers. No stopping those.
This is angled into the batter, it is worked wide of mid on for one. First run of the session.
We are back! Joe Denly and Rory Burns will resume their innings. Josh Hazlewood will start the proceedings after the break. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

A good recovery by England! However, not sure which side will be the happier one at the break. We can easily say it is a shared session. The start though belonged to Australia as the returning pacer, Josh Hazlewood ran riot and took two important wickets of Jason Roy and the skipper, Joe Root. But as the game went on, the pitch played out well for the batters as the movement reduced and batting became easier. Joe Denly and Rory Burns steadied the ship as they are amidst a 50-run partnership. The opener is making most of the life he got, having been dropped on 11 by Usman Khawaja. The two batsmen will be eager to make use of the starts they have got. Also, England would hope they can stitch a big stand here. Australia on the other hand, will look to pick a few wickets quickly after the break. Stay tuned for the second session.
A dot to end! Back of a length on off, this is kept out. THAT IS LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Good comeback! this is on a length and outside off, Burns hangs his bat out and gets beaten.

FOUR! Nicely timed! Just used the pace of the bowler there. Also, the 50-run stand is up and it is a very good one. A much-needed one too as England were in a spot of bother. Fuller and outside off, Burns leans into the stroke and hits it through covers for a boundary.
On the middle pole, Burns pushes it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Burns strokes it to covers.
On the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Attakcs the off pole again, Denly pushes it to covers.
Goes back to bowling length on off, it is defended nicely.
OHHH! Lapse in concentration there for Denly. After a few good balls, Hazlewood bowls it full and outside off, wanting Denly to go for a drive. Joe does so but is beaten.
On a length and around off, this one moves away. Denly guides it to gully.

The inside edge saves Denly there! This is a good nut. It lands on middle and it comes back in. Denly looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Paine and Hazlewood have a chat but don't review. Actually, replays late on show there was no inside edge and it hit him high on the back pad. Also, it was right from Australia to not review as Hawk Eye shows it to be going over.
Good length and on off, Denly tries to defend but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Length ball way too wide for Burns, he lets it be.
This one takes off! Pitching on a length and just outside off, the ball pitches and rises on Burns. He tries to play at it but misses.

Good bowling by Cummins here. The ball pitches on middle and then nips away with the angle. Rory tries to defend but does so inside the line of the delivery. He gets beaten and the ball also just falls short of the keeper as he takes it on the bounce.
Length ball on the fifth stump line, RB leaves it.
Down the leg side this time by Cummins, Rory tries to flick but misses.
Short ball on middle and leg, Burns ducks under it and lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Denly shoulders arms to it.
Full ball on the off side, Denly pushes it towards mid off.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot. They pick up a single.
Edged but safe! Length ball outside off to Burns, the ball gets a thick outside edge and it goes uppishly towards gully but falls short.
Fullish ball outside off, Burns leans into the drive but the shot goes straight to the mid off fielder.
Length ball down the leg side, Rory looks to flick but misses.
Slightly fuller and on off, Denly defends it out.
On a good length and outside off, it has been left alone.
Edgy FOUR! This is shorter and outside off, Denly hangs his bat out, it goes off the outer half through backward point and it races away.
A bumper now on middle, the batter ducks under it.
Another length ball around off, Denly blocks it out.
Hits the length hard on off, Denly defends it out.
Pat Cummins is on now!
Close! This is darted on the off pole. Burns at the very end, gets his bat down and keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Sloppy effort in the field there. This is shorter and outside off, Khawaja goes back and pushes it towards cover-point. Khawaja runs to his right and then dives but fails to stop it.
Well bowled! It is slower through the air on off, Burns lunges and defends it. The ball hits the outer part of the bat and goes towards point.
This is tossed up on off, it is hit towards mid on for another one.
Shorter and around off, Burns goes back and slaps it towards cover. The fielder there misfields and a run is taken.
A short one to end on middle, Denly ducks under it.
On the off pole, blocked again.
Outside off and on a length. Denly shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Creamed! What a shot that is. Not a lot wrong with that delivery. It is slightly fuller and on off, Denly leans into the stroke and hits it through covers for a boundary.
Goes wide of the crease and angles this one into the off pole. JD keeps it out again.
Back of a length and on off, Denly defends it out. The wicket seems to have eased out now and it looks a good one to bat on.
Fuller and flatter this time by Lyon on the off side. Burns sweeps it towards mid-wicket but Head there dives to his right and saves at least two. Good cricket all around.
Good shot by Burns here. He comes down the track to this loopy ball on off and plays it towards deep square leg. The fielder in the deep gobbles it up as the batters take a couple.
Full ball on off, tossed up. Burns blocks this off the front foot.
Short this time, Burns blocks it out.
Flat and on middle, the ball hits the inside edge of Burns' bat and then hits the pad. It lobs up but falls safely.
Shorter in length and outside off, Lyon gets away with it as Burns slaps it to covers.
On the body of Burns, he hops and plays it towards square leg as he retains the strike for the next over.
Short of a length ball on off, Denly punches it towards covers and takes a single.
This time Denly is able to take a couple. Length ball just outside off, he dabs it towards third man and takes a couple.
Hazlewood attacking the stumps here. Good length ball on the off pole, Denly pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball on the fifth stump line, Denly lets it be.
Good ball by Hazlewood to start his second spell. Good length ball on off, it is blocked out by Denly.
Josh Hazlewood is back!
Outside off, Burns pushes it to covers.
FOUR! That has been nailed! Uppish but away from the fielder. Burns brings the sweep shot out. He hits it hard and just away from the diving mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Flatter and on off, Rory pushes it to the man at covers.
On middle, this is defended.
Flatter and on middle, it skids through. Burns goes back and pushes it to covers.
Floats it up on middle, Burns looks to defend but it goes off the inner half to short leg.

FOUR! Edged but Denly won't mind. Good length ball on the off pole, the ball pitches and moves away to catch the outside edge of Denly's blade. The ball though gets enough contact to go away from  the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Full again and on off, this time Burns is able to take the single as he strokes it towards covers.

Great fielding! Matthew Wade is the man. This time Siddle bowls it fuller and on the off pole. Burns comes on the front foot and pushes it towards mid off. Wade at short mid off dives to his right and saves at least one. Putting pressure on the batters here.
Consistent bowling from Siddle, Burns has no business with these kind of balls.
Similar line and length, Burns again lets it be.
Length ball outside off, Burns shoulders ams to it.

NOT OUT! Doing too much, missing leg! Australia lose one review. Denly had a good stride forward there. This is tossed up outside off, it turns back in. Denly looks to flick but misses to get hit on the front pad. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Paine reviews. Replays roll in and Hawk Eye shows the ball to be going down leg.
An appeal for an LBW has been turned down. Australia review. Could just be umpire's call for height or maybe just doing too much.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Tosses this one up on off, Joe strokes it nicely through covers for two. A good shot but Lyon won't mind as he is driving it against the turn.
Loopy ball on off, Denly strokes it to covers.
Fuller on off, this is hit back to the bowler.
Floats it up on off, Denly defends it.

DROPPED! Khawaja is the man! A life for Burns. That went to him quickly but it was at a good height, should have been taken. Siddle's persistence outside the off pole almost paid off. This is on a length and outside off. Burns goes after it. It goes off the outer half to gully who fails to hang on. This could prove costly.
Another one wide outside off, it has been left alone.
Bowls this one outside off, Rory pushes at it tentatively and mistimes it to covers.
Another one on a length and around off, Rory keeps it out.
Back of a length and on off, Burns defends it on the off side.
Good length and on off, this is defended.
Down the leg side, Denly lets it be. Not a lot of purchase in Lyon's first.
This is on middle, Denly works it to the man at mid-wicket.

Just short again! This is floated up on off, it goes on with the arm. Denly plays for the turn but the ball goes off the outside edge. Lands just short of Steven Smith at first slip who wrings his fingers in pain. That hurt.
Flatter and on middle, Burns goes back and works it through mid-wicket for one.
Tosses it up on middle, Burns looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Floats it up on off, Burns pushes it to covers.
Nathan Lyon is on now. The surface seems a touch dry so it will be interesting to see if he gets some purchase.
FOUR! Great shot! This is pure class from Denly. The ball is pitched full and outside off, Denly goes onto the front foot and drives it through the covers for a boundary.
Fuller ball on middle and off, Denly blocks it out.
Full and on off, Burns drives it towards covers and takes a quick single.
Length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
On the off side this one, Burns plays it towards the point region.

Was that dropped or not? Head's reaction says he could have done better. The ball is pitched on middle and leg, Denly flicks it towards mid-wicket and Travis at short leg bends to take the catch but the ball goes from between his legs. The batters take 3 by the time the fielders gather it as the ball rolls towards deep mid-wicket.
Full and on off, Burns plays it straight back to the bowler.

Denly has a bit of a concussion check and hence Drinks have been called for. The good thing is that Joe is smiling, so it does not seem pretty serious. It is the norm these days that if you get hit on the protective gear, a concussion check is made. Also, there is the new rule of a like-for-like substitute if concussion is proved. Coming to the game, well, Australia's morning thus far. They won the toss on a bright and sunny day but the conditions are a mix and match of overcast and sunny. The bowling has been almost perfect with not too many loose deliveries and the hosts have lost two quick wickets. Burns has been impressive with his technique again while Denly has just arrived. Might be lucky that Hazlewood might not carry on for long.

Nasty! Denly wasn't expecting that. Hazlewood pitches this one short and on middle, Denly looks to pull but misses. The ball kicks off sharply and hits the helmet of Denly. It lobs over the slip cordon towards third man. The batters cross and take a leg bye off it. Hazlewood asks Denly whether he is fine and Denly nods, shaking his head slightly.
Length ball outside off, Denly defends it off the back foot.

Ohhh! Edged but short! Close one this. Hazlewood pitches it just outside off, the ball pitches and straightens. It takes the outside edge of Denly's bat and goes towards third slip but falls just short.
On middle and leg, Burns plays it towards square leg and takes a quick single.
Outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Stifled appeal for an LBW by Australia but nothing there. The ball is pitched on middle and leg and angles into Denly. It hits his thigh pad but the ball seems to be going down leg.
Full on middle and leg, Denly defends it back to the bowler.
Full ball outside off, Burns pushes it towards the cover-point region and grabs a single.
Outside off and on a length, Rory shoulders arms to it.
On the off pole, Burns blocks it out.
Full and on middle, Burns pushes it back towards Siddle.
Length ball outside off, Denly lets it be. End of another successful over by Hazlewood.
On the pads of Denly, he beautifully flicks it towards the mid-wicket gap and takes a couple.
Similar line and length again, pushed towards mid off.
This time fuller but on the off side. Pushed back to the bowler by Denly.
Good length ball on the pads of Denly, he looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Joe Denly walks out to the middle to replace his skipper. England need him to play a good innings here.

OUT! LBW! Root is out of here. Not sure why he does not review though. Australia are absolutely pumped up. They have got the big fish. Hazlewood is the man once again. He is making some impact on his return and also, both the wickets are well-deserved. He has been brilliant from the start. He has kept bowling tight, maidens after maidens and also getting the ball to move both ways. This time he gets it to come back in sharply from outside off. Root fails to put bat on ball and gets hit on the pads. An appeal and the finger goes up. Root has a chat with Burns but his partner feels it is not worth the review and he walks back. Replays later on show, that good he did not review as Hawk Eye shows three reds. Australia's decision to bowl first is proving to be the right one here. Till now that is. England in trouble here.
Length ball outside off, Burns guides it towards third man. Good over for England.
FOUR! Great shot! Burns gets on top of the bounce of this length ball outside off and just pushes it through the covers for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, defended on the off side by Burns.
FOUR! Bad start  by Siddle here, releasing all the pressure. This is on the hips of Burns and he glances it towards the fine leg fence.
Length ball on the hips of Root, he flicks it towards deep square leg. The fielder there gives it a chase and gathers it as the batters take a single.
FOUR! A loosener to begin with and Root makes him pay! Shorter and outside off, Root goes back and guides it through cover-point. It races away to the fence.
Peter Siddle is on! First change for Australia.
Fuller this time by Hazlewood, Burns plays it towards mid-wicket. Good over by Hazlewood again.
Loud appeal by Hazlewood for an LBW but the umpire is unmoved. The ball pitches on a length on middle and straightens. It hits Burns on the thigh pad. Looks like would have gone over the stumps.
Length ball outside off, Burns lets it be.
Length ball on middle and off, Burns pushes it towards mid-wicket off the back foot.
On the off pole this time, Burns defends it onto the ground.
Just outside off, Burns covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball this time, hits the inside edge of Root's bat and onto the pads.
FOUR! Action replay of the last ball. Again full and outside off, Root pushes at it with ease and a boundary results.
FOUR! Class from Root! This one is pitched full and on off outside off, Root just leans into the drive and caresses it through covers for a boundary. First boundary of the match.
Length ball outside off, Root gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it out.
A single after 19 balls! Talk about keeping it tight. Length ball just outside off, Burns dabs it towards cover-point and takes a quick single.
Pitched on a length on leg, hit on the hips of Burns as he tries to flick this one towards the leg side.
Well played but for no runs! This is on a length and just outside off, Root dabs it but can't get it past third slip.
Another dot! This is once again on the off stump, Root guides it to point. This is an excellent start by the Aussie bowlers.
Attacks the off pole again, Root is solid in defense.
Good fielding! This is angled into the off pole. Root plays it late towards gully where the fielder dives to his left and stops it.
Fuller in length and on off, Root looks to drive but the bat turns in his hand, he mistimes it to mid off.
Good length and on off, this is defended.
Outside off, Burns looks to defend initially but then bails out.
Short of the fielder again! Around off again and this one also straightens. Rory looks to defend one more time but the ball goes off the outside edge but short of third slip this time.

Edged but well short! Burns played that with soft hands. This is around off and it straightens after pitching. RB defends inside the line, the ball goes off the outside edge but well short of the second slip fielder.
A good short one now on middle, Burns evades it.
Beaten. The ball pitches on a fullish length and swings away from the southpaw after pitching.
On a good length and outside off, Burns lets it be.
The last ball is brought back in from around off. Root once again plays it late and to mid on. A really good over by JH comes to an end. A testing one.
This is tremendous stuff from Hazlewood. A joy to watch this at the moment. The last two balls came in. This one goes out after landing it around off. Root is beaten once again as he tries to defend.
Once again gets the ball to jag back in after landing it on off. Root manages to defend it late.
Now gets this one to angle into the batter, Root defends it.
Very good from Hazlewood. This lands on off and it straightens after pitching. Root looks to defend but is beaten by the movement.
Good length and on off, Root plays it late to the man at gully.
Good running again! This is on the pads, RB flicks it behind square on the leg side and takes two.
Well bowled! He makes good use of the angle. Lands it on off and gets it to slant away. Burns looks to defend but is beaten.
A sharp short one on middle, the batter ducks under it.
On the fuller side and on off, Burns is solid in defense.
Shorter and outside off, Rory does not fiddle with it.
Around middle, Burns defends it out.
On the fuller side on off, Burns pushes it towards cover for one. He is off the mark. A successful first over for Hazlewood.
Back of a length on off, Burns defends it onto the ground.
England are underway! Good running! This is on off, Root drops it on the off side and gets to the other end.
Joe Root is the new man in for England. The skipper will be looking to stay in the middle and steady the ship a bit after the early wicket.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! What a start for Hazlewood and what a start for Australia. Exactly what they would have wanted after electing to bowl. Another excellent delivery. This is on off and on a length, it pitches and moves away. Roy hangs his bat out, the ball kisses the outside edge and goes to the keeper who makes no mistake. A duck for Roy.
That is a beauty! Hazlewood angles this into the batter and then gets it to leave him after landing it on off. Roy looks to defend inside the line and gets beaten.
A loosener to begin with and a loose shot by Roy. Short and outside off, Roy looks to slap it through the off side but misses.
Josh Hazlewood, the comeback man, to bowl from the other end.
A maiden to begin with! On a length and outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Another one on a length and around off, Burns is solid in defense.
A little swing there! This is fuller and around off, it slants away. Burns lets it be.
Three deliveries on a good length and on the stumps, Burns defends it out. Not a lot of movement for Cummins yet.
Another one on a length and around off, Burns once again gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Right on the money to begin with! This is on off and on a length. Burns defends it out.

So all the English players walk out to collect their red caps. That is what they will be wearing on their head today as contribution to the Ruth Strauss foundation. The England players now head back in after collecting their caps and the Aussies make their way to the middle. They are followed by the English openers, Jason Roy and Rory Burns. Pat Cummins to start the proceedings for Australia and he will be bowling to Burns. 4 slips and a gully in place. Here we go...

England skipper, Joe Root, says they wanted to bowl too but it looks a pretty good surface and they want to make use of it this morning. Reckons the toss might just be a good one to lose and a big first innings total is what they are looking for. Further adds the revised conditions were important to take into consideration but they were always going to pick the team from the squad they have. Informs they have two changes, James Anderson and Moeen Ali are out and Jack Leach and Jofra Archer come in.

Australian skipper, Tim Paine says there has been a little weather around, the pitch has been under cover and it is also a shortened game. Informs there is one change, Josh Hazlewood comes in for James Pattinson.

ENGLAND (PLAYING XI) - Rory Burns, Jason Roy, Joe Root (C), Joe Denly, Jos Buttler, Ben Stokes, Jonny Bairstow (WK), Chris Woakes, Jofra Archer ( DEBUT/ IN FOR JAMES ANDERSON), Stuart Broad, Jack Leach (IN FOR MOEEN ALI).

AUSTRALIA (PLAYING XI) - Cameron Bancroft, David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Steve Smith, Travis Head, Matthew Wade, Tim Paine (WK/C), Pat Cummins, Peter Siddle, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood (IN FOR JAMES PATTINSON).
TOSS - Up goes the coin and it lands in the favor of Australia. THEY WILL BOWL FIRST!

Rain, rain go away, let us get some cricket today! The rain Gods have probably listened to our prayers as we have good news to begin with. It is not raining for now and the forecast is also not that bad for today. Since, the 1st day was abandoned, it is now a 4-day Test match. Also, 98 overs are to be bowled on all the days as it is now a 4-day Test match. The second session is an extended one today and an extra 30 minutes is also possible at the end if the amount of overs to be bowled are not done. Welcome to the coverage of Day 2.

Right. England effectively 8/0 at this stage. Roughly 139 overs left in this game, with 41 scheduled to go for tonight. How much of them will we get in? Will the Aussies manage to pick wickets and keep England under check? Will the hosts go all out and try and get to 200 in 2 sessions and then declare, aiming to bowl Australia inside 2 sessions? Or will get a draw? Join us back at 4.30 pm local (1530 GMT) for the final session.

Excellent bowling by England but they were luckless. They could have got Australia all out before Lunch and even after that but the edges either kept getting beaten or finding the gaps. Archer got only 2 wickets but the spell that he bowled post Lunch will be remembered as one of the best ever at this ground. Broad helped himself to 4 wickets while Woakes got 3.

Credit to Australia that they did not lose their way though, even after the Smith retirement. Siddle and Cummins played out valuable time, allowing Smith to get back on the field again. He missed his century by just 8 runs but crucially, took the visitors close to England's first innings total. Do not forget Pat Cummins' contribution as well. The lower order for Australia batted for 132 balls and scored 38 runs between themselves with the bat. That is almost batting out a whole session.

The session started positively for the hosts, with Paine getting dismissed quickly. But then came the fine stand between Smith and Cummins. The pair was starting to counter-attack when Jofra Archer fired in a bouncer. And Smith was down. The crowd got silent as one when Smudge was down but got relieved when he got up. Concussion tests were being taken and Smith was ordered off the field.

End of an eventful session. 5 wickets, 95 runs. Or shall we say 6 wickets? Because Smith was dismissed almost twice. Not a lot to choose between these two sides. The question now is, with 40 overs left in the day and 98 tomorrow, is there still time for a result?

OUT! Caught! Goes for a bumper but this is going down the leg side, Cummins goes for a massive pull to heave this over the mid-wicket fence. He is late into the shot and as the ball passes his attempt, it kisses the gloves. Bairstow goes to his left to grab that easily. Broad has his fourth. England manage to stay 8 runs ahead.
Good length ball on off, Cummins blocks it off his back foot again.
Shortish ball on off, coming in to the right-hander who blocks it off his back foot.
Full and outside off, Hazlewood drives this through the covers and gets a couple. 250 up for Australia! The deficit is now 8.
Outside off, solidly defended.
Down the leg side, Pat looks to flick but misses. The ball goes through the vacant fine leg region and the batsmen take a leg bye.
What will Pat Cummins do now? Go all out?
Spinning in from outside off, worked through square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Josh Hazlewood is the last man in.

OUT! LBW! The decision stays as it is. Leach gets a wicket as well. Full and around leg, Lyon looked to defend but missed and got hit on the pads. leach appealed as soon the ball missed the bat, umpire Gaffaney thought long and hard and then raised his finger. Lyon looked at Cummins and then signalled the 'T'. Hawk Eye comes in and initially we are unable to understand whether the ball has clipped or hit the stumps. Lyon is asked to go and after some time, we come to know that the ball has hit the stumps. No reviews left for Australia now.

OUT! LBW! Lyon has been adjudged and he does look dead plumb. Cummins advises his partner to take the review. Here comes Hawk Eye. Seems like there is some issue because the trajectory is not showing whether it has hit the stumps or clipped. Either ways, Lyon is out. But will Australia lose or retain their review? Okay, it is Hitting. Review lost then.
Jack Leach gets the ball in his hand again. 10-3-16-0 so far. Nice time for him to get a wicket or two.
Outside edge now but doesn't carry. Good length outside off, Cummins fends at this but gets an outside edge. Root is in perfect position to gobble that but it just falls short of England skipper.
Fuller ball outside off, Cummins looked to drive this through the off side but it came off the inner half of the bat to roll towards Broad. On good days, this disturbs the timber.
Another shortish length to which Cummins lunges to block.
Shortish around off, Cummins blocks it off his back foot.
That was in the air! Fuller ball on off, Lyon lofted it towards mid off uppishly but no fielder there. Leach runs from short extra cover to stop the ball. They take three.
Bouncer outside off from Broad, Lyon goes for a pull but misses. Played on a wrong line there.

EDGED, FOUR! Did that carry? Not sure. A length ball outside off, Cummins pushes at it but the ball flies off the outside edge. The ball goes low to Ben Stokes at third slip who gets down to his left but cannot stop it, or catch it. Third man records another boundary. Cummins moves to 20 now.
A length ball, down the leg side, helped through mid-wicket for a run.
Lovely shot but for nothing. Full and outside off, Garry drives this straight back but Woakes bends and stops it with his left hand.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
A length ball around off, solidly defended.

Great catch by Jonny Bairstow! No? My ears are ringing then. A length ball down the leg side, Lyon looked to tuck but missed. Jonny dived to his left and took it with one glove. Went up in an appeal but Woakes says he did not hear anything. Good that Root does not review. Replays show that it went off the shirt.
Bumper again but Lyon is up for the battle. Pulls this towards deep square leg to get a run. Good timing on that one from Lyon.
Fullish on the leg pole, Cummins works it towards fine leg to change ends.
Gets his pull right this time as Broad dishes out another short one, gets off the mark with a single through mid-wicket.
Now a shortish length, on a good height to be pulled but Lyon misses as he gets an inside edge into his body.
That sounded good off the bat but straight to the fielder. Fuller outside off, Lyon punches it straight to covers.
Beaten! That kept low. Fullish length around off stump, Lyon looks to push towards mid on, gets beaten. The ball dies down as it goes to Bairstow.
Fullish one again outside off, Cummins pushes it towards mid off, again came off from the toe end of the willow.
Goes fuller on middle this time, Cummins pushes it straight to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Good length on off, Cummins taps it towards point.
Fullish outside off again, Cummins drives it straight to the cover fielder. Came off from the toe end of the bat.
Slightly fuller on fourth stump, Cummins lunges to block it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on off, Cummins blocks it coming forward.
Going down again, Lyon goes for a flick but misses again.
Going down the leg side this time, misses his flick.
Fullish one outside off, Lyon blocks it well.

Dropped! That was half a chance for sure. Shortish one outside off, Cummins looks to slam this over point but gets an outside edge which flies towards second slip. The ball was slightly higher but Roy couldn't get his jump to perfection and the ball didn't stick in his hands. The batters meanwhile take a single.
Shortish one from Broad, that shaped down the leg side, Cummins looks to tuck it around but missed. No edge there.
Good length outside off, Cummins blocks coming forward. Wanted a single but decided against it.
The batsman has attempted to put bat on ball but fails.
Nathan Lyon is the next man in. This should be done in the next 20 minutes or so.

OUT! LBW! Woakes gets rid of Smith for 92! Wow. That is something unimaginable, isn't it? Steve not getting an Ashes ton. Would have been his third successive ton this series and also the fourth in the Ashes. Would have been the first player ever to do so. Woakes has done the trick. A length ball, outside off, the former skipper gets across but then shoulders arms. Big, big mistake. A rare moment of indecision from Smudge. He is hit on the pads and immediately starts to walks off even before umpire Gaffaney raises his finger. However, Cummins calls him back and asks him to go for the review. Smith's reaction is like, 'Oh, come on, mate! But fine.' Signals the 'T'. Hawk Eye comes in and shows it to be hitting the stumps. End of another knock which has probably saved the day and match for the Aussies. A magnificent 92. Steve Smith departs but only after a standing ovation from the home of cricket. He came out after getting injured and played bravely. Australia now trail by 24. A one-inning shootout awaits us.

Gone, gone, gone! Smith has been adjudged LBW and he immediately starts walking. But Cummins calls him back and the great man takes the review. Looks dead plumb. Yes. Here comes Hawk Eye. Hitting middle stump. Smith misses out on becoming the first ever player to score 4 successive Ashes tons.

A loud appeal for LBW but denied by the umpire. Full outside off, Smith shuffles across, looks for the block but misses. He  gets hit low on the back pad but the impact seems outside off. Replays roll in, and Hawk Eye comes that it was missing the off pole as well. Smith living dangerously here.

FOUR! Full this time outside off, Smith goes for the drive but gets an outside edge on it. The ball goes between gully and the slip cordon towards the third man fence. Looking shaky a bit here Steve Smith.
Smith gets an inside edge and the ball hits him on the pads.

FOUR LEG BYES! Woof! Bairstow will be relieved here as the ball has hit the thigh pad and not on the bat! Down the leg side, Smith looks to flick but misses. The ball hits the thigh pad and trudges towards the fine leg fence.

Good length ball but goes down the leg, Cummins looks to flick but misses. There was a noise but it was probably off the ball kissing the pad. A mild appeal from a few English players but nothing from the umpire.
Slightly short one outside off, Pat taps it towadrs point.
Beaten! Fuller on off, asking Cummins to go for the drive. Cummins obliges to the bowler as he looked to drive but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Wide one outside off, Cummins is not bothered, lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish one from Woakes which came in, Cummins was right behind the line of the ball to block.
Unbelievable. Archer is warming up. Surely Root will not bring him back? Take care of that lad!
Good length outside off, Cummins lets this one go to the keeper.
Short ball just outside off, Smith lets this one go. The man is back to the crease and he is looking for the ton here.

FOUR! Wow, what a return to the crease for this man here! This is just pure class from Steve. Length ball just outside off, goes on the back foot and just creams this towards the cover fence. Consecutive boundaries by Smith.
FOUR! WOW! Who said Smith was retired hurt just a while ago! Length ball on off, Smith clears his front leg and slams this towards mid-wicket. What a shot from Smith that.
Good length ball on off, Smith has his normal walk across to tuck it towards mid-wicket.

Wow. Take a bow. Steven Peter Devereux Smith is walking out to the middle. There is a section of the crowd which is still booing him. But there is an even bigger section, including Aussie and England fans, which is standing up and applauding. Hail the great man.

OUT! Caught! Beauty from Woakes to get rid of Siddle. Shortish length on off from Woakes, Siddle looks to fend at the ball which shapes a tad bit away from him, gets an edge which is pouched by Bairstow comfortably. A dodgy knock comes to an end from Siddle. Australia still trail by 40.
Slightly shorter one on middle, Siddle looks to block towards the leg side but gets a small leading edge that falls close to him.
On a length outside off, Cummins looks to defend but the ball stays low and goes off the outside edge towards cover.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks under the bouncer at the last moment.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.
Outside off, on a length, Cummins looks to play at that but misses.
Length ball on leg pole, Cummins tries to block this one out but he gets an inside edge on it and the ball goes towards square leg.

Huge appeal! Fuller again from Woakes, Siddle looks to flick this with his wrists but is very slow at it. The ball thuds into the pads and England fans make a loud appeal but that looked to be missing leg. No reviews taken. Might have been an edge as well.
Another fuller one from Woakes, Siddle bends down a bit to block it again.
Goes for a fuller on this, Siddle leans forward to block it back.
Michael Atherton on air informs us that Steve Smith is currently undergoing a concussion test in the Australian dressing room.
Another shortish one, looked a slower one. Siddle tucked it towards the leg side bit awkwardly.
Shortish ball on off, came into the right-hander quickly as his flick is missed, gets hit on the back leg.
The weather is playing hide and seek. Bright and sunny now.
Good length outside off, Siddle has no business with that one.
Defended off the back foot by the Cummins.
Beauty! Length ball, fourth stump line, nipping away. A fast bowler's dream! The only thing missing was the outside edge as Cummins looked to defend but did so inside the line. He survives this one.
Full outside off, Siddle drives at this one too. The ball skews off the outside edge and goes between gully and the slip cordon. Denly mops it up from the deep as the batters take three.
Swing and a miss! Full outside off, Siddle looks to drive it through the covers but misses as the ball whizzes past the outside edge. Good bowling by Broad.
On the legs of Cummins, he tries to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. They take a leg bye off this as the ball rolls towards backward square leg.
Outside off, left alone by Cummins.
Stuart Broad replaces Jofra Archer into the attack. 21-5-55-3 so far from him. He will be looking to clean up the Aussie tail quickly here and get a 5-fer also in the process.
Wide outside off, left alone. Woakes starts with a maiden.
Shortish ball on middle, goes further down the leg side as Siddle misses his flick.
Beaten! Outside off on a good length, Siddle looks to push but is beaten. Good delivery.
Shortish length on middle, Siddle pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Fifth stump line outside off, Siddle leaves it alone.

LBW appeal! Woakes starts with a good length ball on middle, this comes in from the off stump and hit Siddle on the pads. An appeal from English players but that looked to be missing leg. Hawk Eye confirms the same.
A dark patch of clouds is approaching the stadium. Hope we do not get any rain. England meanwhile, give the ball to Chris Woakes. 13-3-44-1 so far.

FOUR BYES! Not anyone's mistake, to be honest. Yes, Archer slides this down the leg side but the ball pitches and scoots further away from Jonny Bairstow who cannot get to it with a dive. All the way to the fine leg fence. This stand is worth 11 now.
A bouncer, on middle, PC ducks.
A length ball down the leg side, Patrick misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Around off, solidly defended.
Another one down the leg side, Pat looks to tuck but misses. Archer appeals for a caught behind but nothing from Bairstow.
Full and down the leg side, left alone.
