THE SECOND NEW BALL HAS BEEN TAKEN. Not surprising at all. Archer continues his marathon spell. The deficit for Australia is 48. Critically, there are around 75 minutes in this session. England will aim to wrap this innings up quickly.

FOUR! Much-needed boundary after a long time for Australia. The ball is on the leg side, Siddle nudges it towards fine leg and the ball slowly trudges to the fine leg fence. Burns gives it a chase from square leg but fails to keep the ball in play.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Siddle defends it by getting on the front foot towards the leg side.
On the legs of Cummins, he flicks it towards fine leg for a single.

Some turn off the pitch for Leach, the ball pitches outside leg and goes over the off pole as Cummins misses his defensive block. Bairstow isn't able to grab it on the first time but it doesn't result in any damage.
Pitched outside leg, blocked by Cummins.
Fullish outside off, Siddle pushes it back to the bowler by presenting full face of the bat.
Mixing it up here is Archer, slower bouncer outside off. Siddle evades it.
Now slower yorker from Archer. Siddle read it early to block it well.
Another short ball. Again very high as Bairstow jumps to collect it over his head.
Beaten again! Good length ball on off, comes in with the angle. Siddle looks to have a push at it but gets beaten.
Another bumper! 95 mph this time but too short as Siddle ducks under it.
Blocked towards the point region off the front foot by Cummins.
Quick single taken by the batters. Siddle pushes it towards covers and doesn't react quickly to the call of his partner, however he does make it to the other end in time. Single taken.
Floated this time, pushed back to the bowler.
Again flat on middle, pushed to covers.
Flat on middle, pushed back to Leach.
Flat on middle, Siddle blocks it out towards the off side.
Beaten! Good ball! Shortish length on off, shapes back into the batter who plays down the wrong line to get beaten.
Another shortish one on the body to Cummins, he stands tall to this one and blocks.
Shortish ball on middle to Cummins, Looks to guide towards the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller one to the new man, this one is just outside off, Siddle pushes it towards mid off to take a run. Off the mark on ball one.

STEVE SMITH IS GOING OFF THE PARK. The entire Lord's arena is standing up as one for the great batsman. Don't think he will come out to bat again in this innings. But guess he has done enough to give Australia some well-needed time in this Test. New batsman is PETER SIDDLE. England will now look to bat in this session itself. The lead is 55 for now.

That is nasty. Smith is lying on the ground. He has taken his helmet off. All the English players are going to check on him. The physio is coming running in. England are literally bullying Smith with this short stuff. It is a test of character. A real test. This is going to be a lengthyyy delay....

Nasty! Very Nasty this one by Archer! And Smith is down on the floor this time as the ball has hit him flush on the NECK! Archer bowls this short and just outside off, it shoots off the pitch. Smith looks to duck under it but the ball didn't bounce as much as he expected. He bends down awkwardly in an attempt to leave it but fails to do so. The ball hits him on the side of his neck. He's lying on the ground shaking his head.
This is beginning to be a tough battle.

FOUR! Short again by Archer but pulled well by Smith, just wide of the fielder at backward square leg where Stokes was positioned. The ball was going uppishly and the England players were excited for a moment but the ball races to the fence. 200 up with that boundary.
Fuller this time, Cummins dabs this off his front foot.
Another shortish length on off, blocked by Cummins on the off side.
Same line and length, Cummins is behind the ball to block again.
This is slightly shorter on off, Cummins blocks it again.
Good length ball on off and middle, Cummins blunts it comfortably.
Fuller ball on off, Smith drives it firmly towards mid off and takes for a quick single. There is a direct hit but he is home comfortably.
The batsman fails to put bat on ball.
Again beaten, the wicket doesn't seem to be far away from Archer here. Length ball outside off, Cummins tries to put bat on ball but misses again.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Mixing it up well here Archer. This time Archer bowls it on a length, the ball pitches just outside off and nips away. Cummins tries to defend but misses as he gets squared up.
FOUR! Beautiful drive by Cummins. This time he bowls it full but outside off. Cummins leans into the drive and the ball races to the cover boundary.
Archer bowling short ball after short ball. This time Cummins ducks and it gets through to Bairstow.
Tossed up around middle, Steve drives it straight back. Leach collects and mimes a throw but does not release it.
Around middle, solidly defended.
Full and around middle, this time Cummins nudges it wide of Buttler at short leg for a quick single.
Full on middle, pushed towards the bowler again, this time towards mid on.
Around middle and off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.

Beautiful bowling by Archer! Truly rock and roll! Making life as hard as he can for Smith. Length ball and it rockets off the pitch. It rises on Smith and hits him on the glove.The ball lobs towards Jos Buttler at short leg but just too far from him. He dives but doesn't get to it. Looks like the wicket of Smith is coming soon following the injury on his elbow, however he is toughing it out right now.
Outside edge now! Outside off on a good length from Archer as Cummins looks to push it towards the off side. Gets an edge and lands between slip and gully. They take a run.
Good length on off, Cummins pats it towards point.

Barrage of bouncer continues from Archer, this time to Cummins. The ball flies off the surface as Cummins gets beaten. Bairstow leaps to pouch that one goes for an appeal. Root goes for the review at the very last moment, that looked close. However, replays shows that it was very far from the willow or gloves of Cummins. Review gone for England.

Caught behind! Is it? Archer has bowled a brute to Cummins and there is an appeal for a caught behind. But Aleem Dar has shaken his head. England, after a lot of deliberation go for the review. Here come the replays. And the ball... has hit nothing. Top decision!
Fullish ball on off, Cummins blocks it well but Jofra has overstepped.

Another bouncer! Superb bowling from Archer. This is heading towards the head of Smith, he moves across and looks to hammer over the square leg fielder. Didn't time it well, in the air but lands safe, short of deep backward square leg. They take one.

FOUR! Goes for the bouncer. Archer is not going to stop doing that seeing Smith's pain. Good ball, on the body as Smith looks to pull this, gets a top edge and the ball flies over the keeper for a four. Smith not looking to hang back either.
Cummins flicks this one towards the leg side.
Full on the pads, Cummins pushes it towards mid on.
Full and floated just outside off, it goes uppishly towards point off the leading edge of Cummins' bat.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
This time flatter, Cummins takes a foot forward but gets an outside edge on it. The ball goes off the leading edge towards covers. Falls way short of the fielder.
Floated on middle and off, Cummins plays it back to Leach.

The physio is in the middle. And Smith is wincing. The ball has hit him right on the left elbow. The physio presses a couple of points and the batsman yells in pain. This looks bad. This looks real bad. Looks like England have eventually found a way to get Smith out. Nasser Hussain on air says that the elbow is broken. He takes a couple of pain-killers, does Smith and is ready to guts it out.

OUCH! On the elbow. Wow. Archer has hit Smith on the body and gets the crowd going. Finally gets the line right for the bumper. This doesn't rise much as Smith looks to duck, gets hit on the elbow. Looks in a lot of pain there.
Another bumper but again too high. Bairstow leaps to take it into the gloves.
Outside off on fifth stump, Smith lets it alone.
Slightly shortish but coming into the batsman, Smith blocks it bit awkwardly.
The physio is in the middle. And Smith is wincing. The ball has hit him right on the left elbow.
WIDE! Bumper this time, called wide as Smith ducks.
FOUR! Thumped through the covers. Fuller on but wide outside off. Smith has a chance to open the arms. He slams that one through covers and no one moves. Races to the fence.
Shortish length outside off, Smith walks across and blunts this on the off side.
This time tossed up outside off, pushed to covers.
Full on off, pushed back to Leach.

Ohh! The English team appeal for an LBW but denied by the umpire. Tossed up on middle, the ball goes down with the angle. Cummins looks to flick but misses to get hit on the front pad. The England team appeals in unison but the umpire denies it. The replays roll in and it seems the ball is going down the leg side. Good that the hosts didn't take the review.
Tossed up on middle, Smith pushes it to mid on and takes a single.
Comes forward again and whips it towards short mid-wicket.

Full and around middle, Smith looks to flick but the ball goes off the inside edge, onto the pads and lobs towards short leg. But where is short leg? Has Root missed a trick here? Cummins wnts a single but Steve sends him back.
Jack Leach is back on. 4-2-7-0 so far.

FOUR! What was that? Sharp incoming delivery from outside off, Cummins looks to block it off his back foot but the ball shoots up off the surface to get past the bat. Bairstow fails to collect that even with a leap and it races to the fine leg fence.
Bumper from Archer but too high for Cummisn to do anything there.
FOUR! That was intentional but risky. Fourth stump line outside off, Cummins goes with the shot and manages to thread the slip and gully cordon to get a boundary.
Slightly fuller outside off, Smith pushes it towards cover to take a run.

Good idea from Archer but the line was wrong. Looked for a slower yorker to pin Smith in front of the stumps, misses the line on that one. Remember how Bumrah had got the wicket of Shaun Marsh during Border-Gavaskar Trophy during India's last tour to Australia.
Good length ball outside off, Cummins looked to push it towards point with a dab. Pushed it nicely towards third man. Takes three to get off the mark on first ball.
Outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Smith has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Beautiful flick off the pads! One moment we think he's gonna get out plumb in front of the wickets but he just flicks it gracefully for a boundary. Full and on middle, Smith shuffles across and nonchalantly plays it towards the mid-wicket fence.
Full again outside off, Smith plays this towards covers with just a hint of the outside half of his bat. The ball goes to deep cover where the fielders gobble it up and the batters take two.
Broad bowls this one full and on off, it pitches and stays a bit low. Smith does well to block it towards the off side.
Good length just outside off, Smith blocks it towards point.
Pat Cummins replaces his skipper out in the middle. He will need to partner Smith well.

OUT! Caught! Good captaincy from Root as he persisted with that short leg fielder ever after the 50-run stand. This came in from a slightly shortish length on off, Paine looked to work it towards mid-wicket but gets an inside edge, the ball goes to hit his thigh pad and lob in the air to Buttler who pouches that comfortably at short leg. Early strike for England after Lunch. Archer has his second.
Bumper this time, a bit too high as Paine ducks under it easily.
Shortish one outside off, Smith comes across to work it towards mid-wicket to take a single.
Full ball outside off, Smith pushes it towards point and says a loud no.
Shortish one on middle, Paine pushes it towards deep square leg to take a run.
Good length ball on off, coming into Paine, blocks it towards mid on. Not those convincing blocks though.
Archer from the other end post Lunch.
Pushed to mid-wicket by Smith. Australia start the session well, 5 off the first over after Lunch.
FOUR! Shot of the day! Beautiful straight drive by Smith to this full pitched ball just outside off. It goes rapidly through mid off and to the fence. The deficit is below 100 now for the Aussies.
Outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Fuller this time, Paine pushes to mid-wicket and gives Smith the strike.
Beaten! Good length ball on the fourth stump line, Broad moves his fingers on this one. It pitches and moves away as it beats the outside edge of Paine's bat.
First ball, full toss outside off, Paine fails to make full use of it and pushes it straight to Stokes at cover.

Welcome back to the second session on Day 4 of the second Ashes Test. Stuart Broad will start the proceedings after the Lunch break. Australian skipper Time Paine to face the first ball. Here we go ...
... Day 4, Session 2 ...

Now, when the English side return post Lunch, they would be hoping for heaps of wickets to stand any chance of leveling the series. As far as Australia are concerned, they need one more good session to ensure that the series stays 1-0 going into Leeds. Smith remains the key, actually for England as well. See you on the other side then.

England have not bowled badly at all but just that they couldn't go past Smith. Archer, Broad, Woakes and Stokes bowled brilliantly but without much luck. Broad was the lone wicket-taker for England in this session when he got the outside edge of Wade to be pouched superbly by Rory Burns at gully. However, success has eluded them.

Smith is intact again! Tremendous session for Australia. Just one wicket lost and they have added 75 runs at a decent click. Wade was the only victim the English could claim. It doesn't look like Smith is going to get out. There were a couple of outside edges but Smith is in that kind of a patch where these won't carry to the fielder.  Paine arrived with his share of luck as he missed and edged a couple of balls but has survived. The duo has added 53 runs so far.
Outside edge off the last ball but doesn't carry to the fielder at gully. Smith survives and so do Australia. LUNCH!
Bouncer! Smith ducks this time as he doesn't want to take any risks just before Lunch. 2nd one for the over called by the umpire.
Again on the body, Smith works it towards square leg.
Fuller this time, Smith flicks it towards the leg side.
Short of a length on the body, Paine awkwardly pulls this one towards square leg for a single.
Bouncer but too high for Paine. He tries to hook but misses and the ball carries to JB. First warning for the bouncer given to Stokes.
Good length ball outside off, Smith defends the over out.
Shortish one this time, outside off, Smith blocks it off his back foot.
Fullish one this time, Smith is in total control as he blocks it well again.
Fuller one this time, Smith is right in the line to block.
Good length ball on off, Smith blocks it well.
Full on middle, Smith flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Beautifully driven to the cover fielder off this full ball outside off by Paine.
Paine has played it to the point region.

Beaten! Now, where did this hit Paine, thigh pad, bat or glove? We think it's thigh pad. The ball pitches on a good length, just outside off pole and moves away after pitching. The ball kisses the thigh pad and goes on the bounce to first slip. Oohhs and Aahs by the crowd as well as the players. Paine was looking to defend but got squared up.
Paine shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Length ball on leg again, Smith pulls this well towards backward square leg and gives the strike to his skipper.

Down the leg side, Paine goes for the pull but doesn't time it well. It hits the top half of his bat and uppishly goes towards fine leg. Bairstow gives it a chase, collects it and the batters exchange ends. Leg bye signalled.
Landed outside off, spinning away, Steve gets a big stride forward and watches it go past.
Full and just outside off, blocked towards Leach.
Outside off, pushed towards Leach again.
Full and around off, driven back to the bowler.

FOUR! HEAVED! 25th half-century and 7th in the Ashes for Smith. Good length ball on middle and off, Smith charges down the track to go for the biggie. Doesn't time it too well but good enough for a boundary. Races to the mid-wicket fence. 150 comes up as well for Australia. Smith is in the mood again. He continues to be the thorn for England. First player to score 7 successive 50-plus scores in the Ashes. The 50-run stand comes up too!
Fuller one outside off, Smith comes forward to push towards the off side.
The skipper shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Length ball on the off pole, it nips back in and hits Paine on the thigh pad. The English players appeal for an LBW but the umpire denies it. They surprisingly mull over taking a review as the ball seems to be going well over the wickets. In the end, they decide against taking it.
On middle and leg, Smith flicks this one towards the leg side and takes one. Inching closer to his half ton.
Smith chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
FOUR! Beautiful cover drive by Smith! Full and outside off, perfect for the cover drive and Smith doesn't miss out. Leans into it and smashes it to the fence.
Good length on middle and leg, Smith tucks it towards mid-wicket with soft hands. Runs the first one quickly and completes the second easily. Smith moves to 43 with this.
Fuller one outside off again, Paine pushes it straight to cover.
Fuller one again, Paine blocks this off the inside half of the bat.
Oohhh... that was gone. But for the inside edge. Full and outside off, Paine looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Leach puts in an appeal but no one does. The umpire shakes his head.
Another fullish ball outside off, Smith looks to drive this through point, but straight to Broad who is lazy to get down. The ball rolls towards third man and they take three.
Slightly fuller on middle and leg, Smith works it towards the leg side.
Full on off, Smith comes forward to push it back to the bowler.
This time flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a single. 138/5 Australia with Smith and Paine hanging in.

Ouch! That must have hurt Smith! Stokes has a stare at him. Some fire on the pitch here. Stokes bowls this on a length and just outside off, the ball rises off the deck. It hits Smith between his thumb and forefinger, on his right hand. He has a look at the pitch and then at Stokes, who gives a stare back to him too. Fiery!
Bouncer! Good one and on middle, Smith does well to duck under it.
Similar line and length, Smith shuffles and tucks it towards square leg for a couple. Making good use of the crease here.
Again length but this time straighter, Smith tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Length outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Ben Stokes is back into the attack.
Slightly short one from Leach, Paine looks to slash this but this goes straight to the fielder at point, who fumbles but no run taken.
Another fullish one outside off, Paine pushes it straight to the fielder at point.
Slightly fuller this time on off, Paine comes forward and blocks well.
Another good length ball but on middle and leg, Paine blocks it again.
Similar line from Leach, Smith pushes this towards point.
Good length ball on off and middle from Leach, Paine blocks it by lunging.
Bowling change! Spin for the first time in this innings.
Sun is shining at Lord's at the moment. English weather that, for everyone. It was overcast just a while ago.
Length ball again by the bowler. Smith defends it off the back foot.
Outside off again, Smith lets it go again.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.

What happened there! What a ball by Archer! A seam-up delivery on a length outside off, the ball pitches and nips back in a bit, but just as it crosses Smith, the ball wildly moves to the left of Bairstow. He dives and gets a hand to it as the ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take a bye off it. The ball doing crazy things here.
This one is again on middle pole, the ball pitches and nips back in as Smith gets hit on the thigh pad.
Length ball on off pole, Paine plays it back to the bowler.
Wide outside off to finish the over. Smith leaves it alone.
Good length on middle and off, Smith pushes it towards mid-wicket.

Excellent, simply excellent from Buttler! Wow. What a piece of fielding. Total commitment. Full ball outside off, Paine pushes it towards the off side and looks for a quick single. Ben Stokes comes in from cover and has a shy at the non striker's end, but misses. Paine was in though. No one to backup as Jofra Archer is a bit wide at mid on. The ball races towards the mid-wicket fence but hello! Jos Buttler gives it a chase from deep mid-wicket, dives full length to his left and stops the ball! Three runs taken.
FOUR! SMASHED! Wide ball outside off and a shortish one to add. Paine opens his arms and pummels it through point and cover. Superb shot.
Fuller ball this time, Paine blocks it by staying inside the crease.
Good length outside off from Woakes, leaves it silently.
Signs that we might see spin. Somewhere in the field, Jack Leach is warming up.

Another snorter from Archer, banging it on a length outside off and then generating steep bounce. Paine looks to push at that, almost fending it away, with one hand off the bat but the ball flies off the outside edge. However, because the bottom hand came off the bat, the ball dies down even before it goes to gully. It is in the gap and the batsmen take a single.
Hit this one! What a riposte from Archer. A sharp bouncer outside off, TP sways away from the line.
Archer comes running in but the ball slips out of his hand. Paine threatens to hit that but does not.
Outside off, quietly left alone this time.

EDGED, SHORT! On a length outside off, Tim looks to defend but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge. However, because he played that with soft hands, it does not carry to Jason Roy at second slip.
A short ball outside off, the skipper looks to pull but misses. Was there a noise? Naah...
Full and outside off, left alone.

Similar to the last ball, again Tim looks to push this off the back foot towards the off side. He again gets an inside edge but this time it results in just a single. Luck is favoring Australia here in every way possible.

Ohh! Close one this. Woakes bowls this one on a length on middle. Paine looks to push it towards covers but gets an inside edge on it as the ball rolls towards fine leg. Leach slides in near the fence and keeps the ball in play as the batters take two.
This time full on the off pole, Paine does well to block this towards the off side.
Fuller outside off, Paine blocks it out towards covers.
On the hips of Smith, he pushes it towards square leg with soft hands and takes a single.
Length ball on middle and off, Paine pulls it towards leg for a single.
Beaten! This doesn't happen often but Smith has been troubled twice in this over. Good length ball outside off, Smith plays at a wrong line to get beaten.
This time he attempts a bumper but it is too high. Smith ducks it easily.
Good length ball outside off, Smith lets it be.
Looking for the yorker, Archer dishes a full toss going down leg side, Smith misses his flick on that one.
Shortish one to follow the good length ball, Smith blocks it well.
Good length ball outside off, Smith looks to drive but gets an outside edge. This was a slower one and hence didn't carry to the second slip fielder. That was a knuckle ball from Archer.
Again gets beaten as Paine goes for the push outside off. End of a good over.

Loud appeal by the the English for an LBW but denied by the umpire. They decide not to take the review. Looks to be going above the stumps. Good length ball just outside off, the ball nips back in after pitching. It hits Tim near the knee-roll on the middle pole line. The England players appeal loudly but nothing from the umpire. Replays later roll in and the Hawk Eye confirms that the ball was going over the middle pole. Good decision here.
Outside off, Paine chooses to leave this one.
On middle and leg, Smith flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Beaten! Good ball by Woakes here, pitches it on the fourth stump line and gets it to nip away from Smith. He goes for the block but misses. The ball keeps low and goes to JB on two bounces.
Short of a length ball outside off, Smith plays it back to Woakes.
DRINKS!
Another good length ball outside off, Smith pushes it to mid-wicket to take a run.
Bumper from Archer but too high, Smith not attempting anything on that one.
Shortish length to Paine, who looks to pull and does it awkwardly to get a run.
Good length ball this time, Paine blocks it.
FOUR BYES! Another good length ball on leg stump, shapes away further on the leg side to go to the fence by evading the doing keeper. Paine tried his best to flick but missed.

Ha ha ha! This is comical. How good and honest is this debutant bloke? Good length ball on off and middle, comes in to the batsman. The push towards the leg side was missed and Paine was hit high on the pads. There's an appeal from the slip cordon but Archer is not even interested! Eventually, he appeals, on seeing his mates. Root is serious though and wants to review but is informed that it is too high.
Change of ends for Jofra Archer. 17-7-25-1 so far. Giving Broad a well-deserved rest.
Fullish outside off. A rare edge by Smith but safe as it goes between gully and slip towards the third man region. Denly runs for it from the slip cordon and collects as the batters take two.
Again similar line, on middle and leg, Paine flicks it to the leg side and crosses ends.
Gets on the back foot and flicks this towards fine leg to take a single.
Length ball on off, Smith shuffles across and again plays it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
This time on middle, Smith pushes it back to Woakes off the back foot.
Starts off with a length ball just outside off, Smith flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Chris Woakes to bowl for the first time today. His figures yesterday - 9-3-27-1
Another one outside off on a good length, Paine lets it be.
Fifth stumper from Broad, Paine lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller one this time, closer to the batsman, Paine leaned forward to drive past the covers, got the gap but no timing there, gets a couple.
Shortish ball outside off, closer to Paine who blocks it off his back foot.
Good delivery but equally well played. That came in from a good length ball. Smith lunged to push it towards fine leg to change ends.
Good length outside off, on fifth stump line, Smith leaves this one.
Tim shows the full face of the bat and defends this ball off the back foot.

FOUR! Educated edge this one by the skipper. Good length ball outside off, Paine looks to guide it towards third man but gets a bit of an outside edge. The ball races to the third man fence. The skipper is off the mark but with a bit of luck.

Oohh! Edged but falls safely. Short of a length on middle, Paine looks to pull this one but gets an inside edge onto it. The ball then hits the pads and bounces but falls safely. Close call with short leg in place.
Fuller this time on off, Paine plays this back to Archer.
Length ball just outside off, Paine guides this one to the point fielder.
Good length ball on off, Smith tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single. First run after 18 balls for the Aussies.
Full and around off, this is driven compactly towards mid on. Third maiden on the trot.
By the way, it has gone pretty overcast right now and the floodlights are in effect already.
Outside off, Tim looks to drive but the ball swings back in and goes off the inner half towards Jofra Archer at mid on.
Fuller in length, well blocked out.
On a length outside off, some extra bounce, Tim blocks it out watchfully.
Outside off, the skipper taps it towards cover, looks for a single, then looks at his ex-skipper and is sent back.
Full and outside off, Paine pushes this towards cover.
Outside off, Smith lets it be. Wicket maiden followed up by a maiden. England piling up the pressure here.
That one was awkward. Short of a length on off, Smith lines up for the pull but backs out at the last moment to defend it. The ball kept a bit low and Smith did well to defend it out.
Back of a length this time, Smith defends it towards the point region.
Outside off, Steve shoulders arms to let that one through.
Beaten! Nerves finally getting to Smith maybe. Archer bowls this one wide and short outside off and Smith lashes at it. However, the ball swung away a lot and just beats the blade of Smith.
Good length ball just outside off, Smith looks to defend but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Shortish one outside off, Paine shoulders arms again. Superb over from Broad. Can be the opening England were after.
Fourth stump line on a good length, Paine lets it be.
Looked for another good length ball outside off, dishes a full toss, Paine mistimes it towards mid on.
Shortish one to the skipper to start with. Rises a bit after coming into the batsman, Paine blocks it well.
Tim Paine, the skipper walks out to the middle to replace Matthew Wade. Australia in deep trouble now as they are 5 down and they still trail by 156.

OUT! Caught! Very good low catch at gully from Rory Burns. Broad goes slightly fuller outside off, the length is perfect for the drive and Wade goes for that. The shot produces an outside edge and Burns grabs that inches above the turf. One hand came off the bat when Wade went for the drive. Wade's struggle is over.
Good length ball outside off, Wade is not fending at that.
Good bouncer by Archer, Wade tries to evade it but fails to get out off the way and the ball hits his right bicep. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters cross for a leg bye.
Joe Root has decided to get a bat-pad in now. It is such an underrated position in Test cricket.
Full on middle and off, Steve flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Just outside off, Smith shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on off, pushed towards cover. The fielder there stops it.
Good bumper. Hits the deck hard on the middle pole line, Smith ducks under it as the ball is collected by Bairstow.
Archer steams in, bowls this one just outside off on a good length. Smith lets it be.
Good length ball outside off, Wade is aware of his stumps as he lets this pass to the keeper. Another one shaped into the left-hander. Tight over from Broad.
Good ball! Fullish one on middle, Wade lunges to block it.
Good length ball, on the fourth stump, came slightly in to the batsman who blocked it well of his back foot.
Full ball on middle to Wade, he flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
This one is again on a good length, closer to Smith who tucks this towards square leg to take a single. 100 up fur Australia with that run.
Good length outside off, Smith has no business with it. After pitching shaped further away.

Ouch! This bounces rapidly towards Wade, he is hit on the gloves. The ball rolls towards the leg side. It seems that the ball hit Wade on the fingers, he takes off his gloves and stretches them, he seems alright as he puts his gloves back on quickly.
This time just outside off, blocks it out.
On middle and leg, Wade this time shuffles across and plays it towards square leg.
Good length and on off, pushed towards mid off.
Bouncer! Well directed by Archer, on off pole line. Wade ducks under it.
Good length ball on off, Smith shuffles across and tucks it towards fine leg. Crosses ends.
Just 1 over for Stokes today as Jofra Archer is into the attack.
Fullish on off, Wade flicks it towards short mid-wicket. End of a good over for Australia. 9 off it.
FOUR! Fuller one outside off to the left-hander, Wade punches it through mid off superbly. Archer dives to his left to stop but fails to do so. Wade reaches 1000-run landmark with that boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Smith pushes it towards mid-wicket to change ends.
Beaten! Superb comeback! This is again on a shortish length, shapes away from the batter, Smith fends to get beaten.
Slightly short this time outside off, Smith blocks this towards leg side off his back foot.
FOUR! Superb timing from Smith. Good length ball outside off, Smith punches this through point to get another boundary. No chance for the fielder there.

Fractionally short on middle and leg, Smith gets on one foot and pulls it towards deep square leg. He runs quickly for the first and thinks about going for the second, but decides against it. Tidy over from Stokes, just 2 off it. Australia are 89/4.
Full on middle and leg, Wade flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Good length ball just outside off, Matthew shoulders arms to this one.
Again full outside off, this time Wade lets it be.
Fuller this time just outside off, Archer makes a good stop at mid off.
Outside off on a good length. Wade leaves it alone.
This one is closer to off pole on a good length, Smith blocks it well and does his antics.
FOUR! Top shot! Shortish length outside off, Smith punches this off his back foot through covers to hit the first boundary of the day.
Fifth stump line on a good length, Smith leaves this alone.
WIDE! Goes for the bouncer but not the right line, too wide down the leg side, Smith ducks under it.
This is on a shortish length on off, Smith blocks again.
Another one on the same line, Smith walks across and blocks it off his back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Smith looked to play at it but kept the bat just away. Good delivery from Broad.
Stuart Broad from the other end for England.
Again on middle and off, Wade blocks it out towards off. 2 runs off the over.
Good length ball on off, Wade defends it out.
This time on middle, Smith flicks it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Good bounce on this ball. It pitches on a length outside off, Smith awkwardly defends it out. It hits the handle of Smith's bat.

Length ball above the hips, Wade looks to flick and the ball hits Wade's gloves. The ball rolls towards square leg and the batters cross for a single. Wade is off the mark after 23 balls. Wade wrings his hand in pain.
Out come Steve Smith along with Matthew Wade. Ben Stokes will continue from where he left off yesterday to start the day. Matthew Wade on strike and here we go...

A crucial day awaits us as the Three Lions will be going all out attacking in order to level the series while the Men Down Under will try everything possible (also praying to the rain gods) to ensure that doesn't happen.

As it stands, Australia trail England by 178 runs and they have lost 4 wickets as well. The good news for them will be that Steve Smith is still at the crease and if he plays another innings like he did at Edgbaston, Australia can again get the advantage. Coming onto the hosts, they will be unhappy with the rain gods interrupting their momentum on Friday as they were ripping through the top order of Australia. Everyone in Australia except for Smith, were struggling to deal with the swinging conditions and given more time, the English pacers will be confident of dismissing the visitors early today.

Welcome to Day 4 of the 2nd Ashes Test. The match hinges in the balance right now as 5 sessions out of 9 have been washed out. However, in those 4 sessions that happened, 14 wickets have been taken so we are expecting another day which will be dominated by the ball.
... Day 4, Session 1 ...

What's in store for day 4 then? If we get a full day's play, we might stand a chance of having a result or else we are in for a draw. Let's hope for the former and if that happens, England would have to bundle Australia quickly and score some quick runs to give themselves a good enough total to defend. And obviously, bundle Australia out, again. As far as the Aussies are concerned, they would want to bat out a couple of sessions tomorrow to keep an upper hand in the series. Join us for the 4th day of this match at 1100 Local (1000 GMT) and let's pray that we get a great and FULL day of play. Till then, cheers!

Today's play consisted of just one session but it was an eventful one as after a good start from Khawaja and Bancroft, Australia found themselves at 71/4. Smith and Wade held out until Lunch with Wade yet to get off the mark. The English bowled beautifully as they didn't let any of the batters settle and were duly rewarded. Archer got his maiden Test wicket as he dismissed Bancroft and brought an end to the 49-run second-wicket stand. Broad and Woakes took one wicket each as well.

STUMPS! Yawn! It has been a tiring time since Lunch as both the sessions after that have been washed out. As it stands, it seems like only one result is on the cards (draw). Unless a dramatic collapse from either side happens, the match is just going to be stretched out. Six sessions of play remain and with two-and-a-half innings to go, a result doesn't seem possible from this match.

1540 Local (1440 GMT) - Early Tea has been taken on the third day as the rain continues to pour down. No positive news to look forward to as well, as it is gloomy all around England and the forecast says that there are no signs of the showers going away anytime soon. However, Australia will be happy with this as another session of play is washed out and just seven sessions remain. Meanwhile, the task for England gets tougher with the match heading towards a draw when they clearly had the upper hand.
Update 1420 Local (1320 GMT) - And it continues. Nothing positive to update as rain continues to pour down in London.

Australia may not might mind it too much. They were certainly up against it and would love if a session or two gets washed out. That means facing England bowlers for a lesser amount of time. Not much batting left any which ways...
Welcome back. Er... go back. Nothing much to report. The rain is steady and we are definitely not going to resume on time. The wait begins.
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

Rain has arrived and the forecast says that there will be heavy rains. England would want to come into the middle as soon as possible and make further inroads in the Australian batting line-up. Interesting to see if we can start on time post Lunch. Join us back for the second session at 1340 Local (Hopefully).

Who goes happier into Lunch then? Any doubts? Well, England have taken 3 already and Wade is just surviving. However, Smith is again into the act. He is batting on 13 and hasn't been troubled much. But all the others were troubled by the English bowlers. Archer and Broad started the proceedings exactly the way they finished yesterday. But Bancroft and Khawaja did well to see off the initial hour. However, Archer eventually got the better off Bancroft to claim his maiden Test wicket. That brought a mini collapse as Australia slipped from 60/1 to 71/4 in the span of 45 balls.

Right. Pretty punctual rain clouds. It was forecast that it would begin to rain around 1 pm and boy, has it been proved right. The forecast is very iffy for the rest of the afternoon but the ground has excellent drainage. So, if the rain does stop, it should not take too long to resume.

Well, just one ball bowled in the over and umpire Aleem Dar has called for the covers. The persistent drizzle has just gotten to heavy to continue playing. LUNCH WILL BE TAKEN AS WELL, with just 4 minutes to go for the break.
Good delivery! Good length on off, goes a bit away from the batsman. Wade knows his off pole and leaves it alone. Also, drizzle getting heavier.

Some sawdust is being applied on the landing area of the bowler. Oopss... a spectator is unable to fold his umbrella and it breaks! Just a sign of the heavy wind. Might be a good one, because it means that the clouds could be blown away.
A hat-trick of leaves to end the over.
Outside off, left alone again.
Outside off, another exaggerated leave from SS.
FOUR! A bit too straight from Broad, the length being a bit too full as well, Smith gets across and tickles it to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 178.
A bouncer down the leg side, Steve ducks awkwardly.
A length ball outside off, Smith gets across and tucks it towards square leg.

Wade survives! Stokes steams in and pitches this full on leg, Wade looks to flick it but misses again to get hit on the pads. The England team put in a loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Wade has a quick look at Smith as he thinks it was pitching outside leg and Smith agrees. They go for the review, replays roll in and Hawk Eye shows that the ball was pitching outside leg. Two reviews taken by Australia and neither lost although one resulted in the dismissal of Bancroft. However, this time Wade survives and Australia breathe a sigh of relief.
Wade has been adjudged LBW! He has taken the review though. Seems to be pitched outside leg. And Hawk Eye confirms...
Ouch! That must have hurt quite badly. It pitches outside leg and Wade looks to flick towards fine leg but misses to get hit on the glove.
Full ball on the off side, played towards covers.
Short and Wide to Wade this time, he moves away from it and leaves it alone.
Fuller this time just outside off, Wade lets it through to JB.
Length ball on middle, Smith shuffles across and tucks it towards deep square leg for one.
Fuller from Broad to Wade as he leans into this cover drive and times it superbly but can't go pass the diving fielder at covers. Very good stop that.
Good length outside off, Wade leaves this alone.
Another fuller one on middle, Wade leans forward to block it.
Fuller on from Broad this time, Wade looks to power this through point but finds the fielder. The ball was in the air but pretty short.
This is on fifth stump outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Wade pushes this to mid-wicket for nothing.
Again outside off, Smith leaves it alone. Stokes starts off with a maiden.
Well left this one by Smith. Pitched on a length outside off, Smith lets it through.
Again length ball on off, defended towards the off side by Smith.
Length ball on off, Smith defends it from within the crease.
Full around off , Smith comes down the track and defends it towards mid off.
Beaten! Stokes starts well as he bowls this one on the fourth stump line and gets it nip away from Smith. He squares him up and beats the outside edge.
Ben Stokes into the attack now as England have the momentum.
Good length ball outside off, Wade works it on the off side. Yet to open his account after 11 balls.
On a good length again coming into the batsman, Wade works it towards point and looks for a run but there is no run. The fielder has a shy at the stumps there but Wade was well in.
Good length on middle, Wade lunges to work it towards leg side.
Goes wider this time on a good length, Wade lets it be.
Good length ball outside off, Wade looked to play at it initially but left it alone later.
Good length on off, comes into the batter who blocks it off his back foot.
Shortish length on middle, Smith works it straight to Jofra Archer at mid-wicket.
The umbrellas are opening in the stands...
On fifth stump line this time, Smith is not worried and lets this go.
Fuller this time, Smith blocks it coming forward.
Shortish one again as Smith looks to open his arms and smash it through point. Finds the fielder though.
Wide outside off on good length. Smith leaves this alone.
FOUR! Smashed! Shortish one to Smith from Woakes which rises just perfectly for Smith to pull this through square leg and collect a boundary. Very good shot.
Fifth stumper this time on a good length. Wade leaves this alone. A wicket maiden from Broad. Australia need runs from this partnership. England need Smith. Period.
Fuller this time and it is on the middle, Wade leans into his shot to push this towards mid on.
This is on good length but again wide of off stump, Wade leave this alone too.
Slightly fuller outside off from Broad this time. Wade knows his off stump as he lets this go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, came into the batsman, Wade blocks this one off his back foot.
Matthew Wade walks in amidst a plethora of crisis.

OUT! LBW! Australia lose their fourth wicket and third of the day. Loud appeal by England. Looks plumb to the naked eye but umpire Aleem Dar has denied it. The ball pitches just outside off and goes in with the angle. Head tries to block it out but misses to get hit on the front pad. Broad and the whole team are in disbelief as Aleem Dar denies the appeal. The umpire feels that there were two sounds but the replays show that they were of the ball hitting the front and then the back pads. Root gives the 'T' and reviews it straightaway. The Hawk Eye comes in and shows three reds as the ball is crashing into the middle pole. Head is a goner. They have lost 3 quick wickets in the span of 11 runs with the deficit still 187. England are well and truly on top here!

That's out. That's out. That's so so out! Aleem Dar has turned down an appeal for LBW against Travis Head. Stuart Broad is shocked (as always) but this time the whole team supports him in that shock. Up goes Root's signal for the 'T'. Here comes Hawk Eye. Missing off. Missing leg. CRASHING into middle. Off goes Head. Thank god for reviews...
Again wide and on a length outside off, Smith again leaves it.
Outside off, Smith leaves this one late outside off.
Again full and on off, Smith blocks it out.
Jack Leach is getting ready to bowl it seems. He is getting loose at his fielding position.
Fuller, much fuller outside off, Smith blocks it out towards covers.
This time on the legs of Travis, he clips it towards square leg and takes one.
Beaten! Good length ball on middle and off, it pitches and nips away from Head. He tries to block it out but does so inside the line and misses.
Good length ball on off again from Broad as Smith is ready to leave it alone. He does his usual walk across on off side as he leaves this, the ball clips Smith's pad on its way to the keeper.
This is closer one but still wide for Smith to play it it, lets it through to the keeper.
This time a good length ball outside off, Smith leaves it again and then does his circus with the bat.
Goes at the stumps this time from a shortish length, Smith works it towards square leg to take couple of runs.
Another one on the same line, goes further away as it passes the batsman, Smith is not fending at those.
Broad starts with a wide outside off delivery which is on the fifth stump, Smith lets this go to the keeper.
Stuart Broad is back for another spell. 8-0-20-1 so far.
FOUR! Much better this time by Head. This again on a length, but outside off. Head goes onto the back foot and punches it towards covers and the ball races away to the fence.

Great fielding and bowling here from England. Woakes bowls this one on a length on middle and off, the ball pitches and straightens. Head tries to push it towards covers but gets an inside edge onto it as the ball rolls towards fine leg in a jiffy. Leach there runs to his right, puts a dive in and again saves two runs for his side. He has been fielding well there throughout the day. Head gets off the mark, but in unconvincing fashion.
Full ball outside off, Head lets it through to JB.
On the hips of Smith, he works it round the corner towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Good length outside off, Smith lets this go through to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Smith blocks it well and then does his antics.
Down the leg side, Head looks to flick it but misses.
Again this time full on the off pole, Head defends it towards point.
Full and way outside off, Travis lets it be.
Fuller this time and on the middle pole, Head is late to bring his bat down and gets an outside edge on it as the ball rolls towards cover-point.
Length ball outside off, Head lets it go but is a tad bit late in doing. He should be more careful about it.
We are in for a slight delay as the physio is looking after Bairstow's thumb. Meanwhile, the umpires have called for the Drinks Break.

Good length delivery outside off from Archer, Head leaves this ball alone. That shaped a tad away from the batsman and Bairstow failed to collect it cleanly and he gets hit on the thumb. He looks in pain there, taking his time.
Again outside off, Smith leaves it again. Maiden by Woakes. England continue their consistent bowling.

Unorthodox leave by Smith to this length ball outside off. But well, that's his way and if one looks at the results it has given him no one would be too unhappy about it. Smith and his leaves - very peculiar. Takes his bat skywards and after the ball passes, brings the willow down like attempting to swat a fly.

Loud appeal by England but turned down. This time down the leg side, Smith looks to flick this one but misses. The ball hits the thigh pad and Bairstow dives to his left and grabs it. The English players appeal as they thought there was some bat on it but the umpire disagrees.
This time on a length, the ball pitches outside off and comes back in. Smith offers the leave but gets hit high on the thigh pad outside off.
Another length ball outside off, Smith again defends it towards covers.
Good length ball just outside off, Smith blocks it out towards the off side.
Too high! Archer bangs this short but it is too high, Bairstow leaps to get a hand to it. The batters looked for a run but decided against it.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
This on the hips, comes in from good length on middle as Head pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Travis is nowhere close to the ball as he looks to defend and is comprehensively beaten.
Beaten! This kept slightly low. Outside off on a fuller length as Head looks to play at it to get beaten.
Smith is off the mark. Good bowling this from Archer. On middle but shortish in length, Smith works it awkwardly towards leg side to take a run.
Good length on fifth stump line, Head is not going to fend at that.

MIX-UP, SAFE! Nervy moments for Australia. Full and around middle, stays low, Head crouches to flick this towards square leg and sets off for a single. Smith immediately responds but then Travis changes his mind. Steve has to go back and the throw comes at the bowler's end but misses. Smith was in anyways.
Beaten! What a beauty from Woakes! Shortish length on middle, squares up Head completely as he looks to fend at the ball. Very close to getting an edge and have some early lunch with Khawaja.
Good length ball outside off to Head first up, he leaves this alone through to the keeper.
Travis Head comes in at number 4, replacing Khawaja.  The rain is falling a bit heavier now...

OUT! Caught! Khawaja is out of here now! Good length ball outside off, Khawaja pokes at the ball with no feet movement whatsoever. There is an outside edge Bairstow is not going to drop that. Australia in a spot of bother here. Second wicket in the span of 4 balls and we now have two new batsmen in the middle.
Shortish length on off, shapes away from Khawaja who lets it be.
Outside off on a length, Smith leaves his first ball alone. Finally a successful over for England and Archer is the man. Wicket maiden it is for the youngster.

Last game's centurion Steve Smith to join Khawaja in the middle now. Smith vs Archer now! What has Root set for him? Two slips, a short leg and a leg slip. Here we go... the most awaited contest of this week...

OUT! LBW! Archer gets his first Test wicket! A gritty innings by Bancroft comes to an end and so does the 49-run stand between Khawaja and him. Jofra bowls this one on a good length outside off. The ball nips back in after pitching and the ball hits the pads of Bancroft, as he shuffles across the stumps in his usual way, attempting to block this one out. However, he does so outside the line and is caught in front of the wickets. Jofra straightaway runs to the keeper in celebration and then appeals. Umpire Aleem Dar does not even wait a second in raising his finger. Cameron is a touch disappointed, looks at the pitch for a while and then towards Khawaja. He feels it might be too high and after some discussion, goes for the review. Hawk Eye shows that the ball has pitched outside off, impact is in line and the ball is clipping the bails of the leg and middle poles. Bancroft might consider himself unlucky here. He fought a battle out there, staying out there for so long and this was one such decision which could have gone either way. England get the breakthrough that they dearly needed and Australia lose their first wicket of the day. The deficit is 198.
'Looks a bit high!' says Bancroft to Khawaja. Cameron has been adjudged LBW here by Aleem Dar. Here comes Hawk Eye. Clipping the top of the stumps! Review is not lost but Bancroft's wicket is...
Defended off the back foot by Bancroft.
Another good bouncer by Archer. Bancroft ducks under it.
Bowls another length ball here and it hits Bancroft in the box. Painful but he is okay.
Archer continues here. Bowls a length ball here and it hits Bancroft on the thigh pad.
Another good length ball outside off, Khawaja lets this go to the keeper again.
Good length ball on off, it shapes away further from the left-hander who shoulders arms again.
This is slightly short but is on middle, Khawaja blocks off his back foot.
Another one on fifth stump line but shortish in length, Khawaja has no business with it.
Fifth stump line outside off, Khawaja leaves this alone.
Ohh! That was very close. Good length ball on off, goes slightly away from the batsman as he lets this go. Looked in two minds there but left it alone eventually.
Fuller this one near the pads, Bancroft pushes this one through mid on where Broad gives it a chase and the batters take a couple. Australia cruising along apparently.
Oohh! Bancroft looks to flick this leg side ball on the pads and misses. Some noise on that but looks like it hits the pads of Bancroft.
Bouncer and Bancroft does well to evade it. The ball goes through to the keeper.
Outside off length ball, CB lets it go.
Good length just outside off, Bancrofts gets squared up on this one and the ball hits the outside edge of his bat. However, the ball just goes onto the pitch. Oohs and Aahs by the English.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Cameron.
This is fuller on middle, Khawaja flicks it to mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter outside off from Woakes, Khawaja with a chance to open his arms. He goes with the short and slams this through point for a boundary. Third of the over.
FOUR! This time bowled shorter and outside off, Usman stands tall and punches it towards the cover-point fence.
Good length ball on middle, tucked towards square leg by Usman.
This is slightly fuller from Woakes, Khawaja again gets an outside edge but the ball doesn't carry to third slip.

FOUR! Lucky boundary! Woakes starts with a good length ball on middle, Khawaja looks to defend but gets an outside edge which goes wide of third slip. Races to the fence. 50 up for Australia. They trail by 208 runs.
Short spell here for Broad as Woakes comes into the attack now.
Bouncer and Bancroft does well  to get out of the way as he ducks and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Wide down the leg side, the batsman leaves it alone.

FOUR! Edged this time but runs for Bancroft. First boundary in 53 balls for Bancroft. Wow, that took a while! Bowled full and outside off, Bancroft goes for the cover drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball races behind third slip towards the third man fence for a boundary. Streaky but will do for the Aussies.
FOUR LEG BYES! Again near the hips and waist of Bancroft, the ball hits the waist and rises off it over the keeper's head, racing towards fine leg fence.
Short of a length this time and it hits Bancroft on the side of his stomach as he misses his flick towards fine leg. Looks to be in a little bit of pain here Bancroft.
Good length ball on off pole, Bancroft defends it towards the off side.
This one is drifting in towards the stumps, Khawaja blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Khawaja pushes it towards covers.

Goes for a shorter one this time but the line is not right as Khawaj swivels to pull this through square leg. The ball was racing to the fence but Jack Leach hared at it from fine leg to make a diving stop. Stops two there.
Good length again from Broad, he is looking to hit the pads of Khawaja who again leans forward and blocks it well.
Goes for a fuller one on middle, Khawaja defends this solidly again.
Shortish length coming into the left-hander, Khawaja blocks it off his back foot.
This time Bancroft manages to defend it as he gets right behind the line of the delivery on middle. The plan for England should be to bowl Archer in short and impactful spells.
Beaten! What a ball by Archer! Again similar line and length, this time the ball leaves Bancroft's bat. He is squared up and the ball goes past the outside edge.
Good ball by Archer, pitching on off, it nips in towards Bancroft. He misses the ball and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off again but this time fuller, Bancroft places it towards covers.
Outside off, CB shoulders arms to this one.
Short ball just outside off, Bancroft ducks away and lets it through to the keeper.
Beaten! First one of the day. This was on fourth stump line outside off, Khawaja looks to fend at it and is beaten. Lucky not to edge there.
Dishes this on a fuller length again which was coming into the batsman, Khawaja pushes this to mid-wicket.
Fuller on again outside off, Bancroft tucks it towards cover to change ends.
This is slightly fuller as Bancroft looks to defend but manages it with inner half of the bat.
Another good length ball, coming into the batsman, Bancroft blocks it by leaning into the shot.
Starts the second over with a good length ball outside off, Bancroft lets it go through to the keeper.
Well bowled bouncer by Archer on middle and leg, it hits the shoulder of Khawaja and goes to the keeper. England appeal but nothing doing for the umpire.
Outside off and on a length, Khawaja leaves it.
Down the leg side, Khawaja looks to flick but misses.

Close one this for Bancroft. He shuffles across the stumps to block this one out but gets an inside edge on it. The ball rolls uppishly towards fine leg as the batters cross and take a single. There was a leg gully in place and the ball was not far away from him. Also, had Bancroft missed, it might have been plumb in front of the wickets.
Wide outside off, Bancroft lets this one through.

Plenty of predictions, at least here in our com box. Selfie, who likes taking pictures of mother nature with himself taking centrestage, has a smile on his face looking at the skies at Lord's considering that he himself is a fast bowler. 'Lovely conditions to bowl', he says. Then his face contracts a little (because he is an Aussie supporter) and adds, 'I feel England will bundle out Australia cheaply'. Another one, Suraj, reckons that it is going to be Cameron Bancroft's day as he finds his luck similar to that of Rory Burns. Interesting thoughts...
Good ball, full and on a driving length by Archer. Bancroft plays it towards mid off.
Archer to share the ball with Broad from the other end.
Wide outside off, Khawaja lets it go. Comfortable start for Australia so far.
Pitched just outside off on a length, the ball shapes back in a bit and misses the stumps by a small margin. Khawaja was sure where his wickets are and lets it go.
On the leg side, played to square leg.
Again on the hips, played to mid-wicket by Usman.
Similar ball again, angling into Khawaja from Broad, he again flicks it towards fine leg and takes a couple.
Good length ball on the pads, Khawaja tickles it off his pads towards fine leg to start off the day with a couple. Leach dives and keeps the ball in play.

'Looks to be a bowling day,' says David 'Bumble' Lloyd on air. And he ain't incorrect. It is a gloomy morning, with plenty of overcast skies and Australia will have a pretty stern examination of their batting technique. Here is Stuart Broad to UK in the UK, with three slips in place. Here we go...

Australia should consider themselves really lucky that they lost just one wicket yesterday as the ball was moving a lot. The first hour today will be crucial for them because if they lose wickets early on, the tide could completely swing England's way. Let's wait and see how the Aussies respond in these testing conditions.

Yesterday, one can say that both the sides shared the day. England were 26/2 before Burns and Denly steadied the ship with a 66-run stand. They again had a collapse post lunch, but Bairstow and Woakes again stitched up a partnership of 72 runs as they took England from 138/6 to 210/7. Burns and Bairstow both scored half a ton as England crossed the 250-run mark. For the Men Down Under, it was a good day of bowling as Hazlewood, Cummins and Lyon took three wickets apiece, and Siddle took one. The fielding department was a mixed bag for Aussies as they dropped Burns on 11 and then on 47, but Bancroft made amends by taking a blinder to dismiss him later at short leg.

At the end of day 2, Australia are 30/1 and trail the English by 228 runs.  The Aussies lost the wicket of Warner late in the day yesterday and suffered an early setback in their innings. Broad and Archer bowled well towards the end and will be looking to continue their good momentum. Khawaja and Bancroft, on the other hand, will be looking to provide a solid foundation to the Australian innings and cut the deficit as much as they can.

Good morning and a warm welcome, or should I say a cloudy welcome to the third day of the second Ashes Test. We do have good news for you, as it seems like play will start today on time as well. However, there are forecasts for showers later today so let's keep our fingers crossed.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Australia in reply, have lost Warner early but Bancroft and Khawaja have done well to ensure no more wickets fell. On Day 3, the wicket will probably be easier to bat on at the start and Australia will hope to cash in. England on the other hand, need to keep taking wickets regularly and hope to go into their second innings with a lead. There is rain predicted on Friday but we should get play. Do join us for the action which begins at 1100 local (1000 GMT). Till then, take care and goodbye!

The day began with Australia winning the toss and electing to field. They had England on the mat at 138 for 6 but then Bairstow along with the lower order took England to a very competitive total. He scored a half ton along the way and was the last wicket to fall. For Australia it was a combined effort from the bowlers but Cummins and Hazlewood were probably the pick. The latter ran through the top order and the former took wickets of the batters from the middle order.

A very entertaining day of cricket today! The match is evenly poised at the moment. Yes, Australia did lose Warner but Cameron Bancroft and Khawaja hung in there, survived the hostile bowling from the England pacers and have brought down the deficit to 228.
On the off pole, defended. That is it for today. STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Way down the leg side, Bancroft looks to flick but misses. Bairstow does well to make a half stop diving to his left. No runs conceded.
Shorter and on the body, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, Khawaja strokes it down towards long on for two.
The batsman has been struck on the thigh pad.

Good running! You don't see batters running 4 runs these days, do you. This is full and on the pads of Khawaja, he flicks it towards mid-wicket nonchalantly and sets off. Buttler from short leg goes running to collect the ball near the fence and does so but by then the batters had run a quadruple.
Length ball on the leg side, it hits the thigh pads of Bancroft and the ball rolls towards the vacant short leg.
It is a back of a length ball by Woakes, Bancroft is early into the shot and gets a thick outside edge as the ball rolls towards third man.
Similar line and length, CB again defends it nicely.
Good length ball on middle and off, Bancroft moves across the stumps and blocks it out back to the bowler.

Shorter and around off, comes off slow of the surface. Khawaja is early in the pull. It goes off the toe-end and falls short of Roy at second slip. He gets a hand to it but can't stop it. It goes towards third man for one. Second slip does the mopping up job.
On a good length and around off, Khawaja blocks it out.
Bancroft leaves this one alone. Archer finishes off a very good over.
BEATEN! Another beauty by Archer. He bowls this just outside off on a good length, forcing the batsman to come onto the front foot. Bancroft plays at it but misses as the ball straightens very late.
Mixing his length up nicely here Archer, this time bowls full. Cameron gets his bat down in time.
Bowls this one short on the leg pole line, Bancroft ducks and lets it through to the keeper.
Another length ball outside off, CB lets it be.
Shorter and on off, Bancroft stands tall and pushes it to covers.
Change of ends for Jofra Archer.
Again wide outside off, UK lets it through to the keeper.
Another beauty by Woakes, Khawaja leaves this one again but it hits him on the stomach. He's playing dangerously right now.
No run. The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Length ball outside off, the batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.

Good leave or not? Well we can't decide on this one. The ball is pitched on middle and off, it straightens after pitching. Khawaja shoulders arms to it but the ball goes from just above the stumps. Too close for comfort.
Good length ball on the hips of Khawaja, he nudges it towards fine leg and takes a couple.
Chris Woakes is on now! He has a brilliant record on this ground. England would love for him to take a wicket at least.
Once again looks to hit the pads of Bancroft as Broad goes full and on middle. CB gets his bat down in time and works it to mid-wicket.
Works it with the angle towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
This is on off, Khawaja is solid in defense.
This is angled into the pads of the batter, he works it through mid-wicket for one.
This is angled into the pads, CB defends it out.
Good running! Back of a length ball on off, Khawaja taps it towards cover for one.
On middle again, this is shorter. CB nudges it to short leg.
Looks to hit the pads of Bancroft as he bowls it on middle, Cameron gets his bat down in time and works it to mid-wicket.
Well bowled again! On off and once again the ball straightens and causes problem for the batter. CB defends the original trajectory but is beaten.
Good length and outside off, left alone.
A short one on middle, too high. Bancroft evades it. JB leaps and collects it nicely.
Well fielded! This is fuller outside off, Bancroft looks to drive but it goes off the inner half to the right of short leg. Buttler sticks his hand out and stops it.
FOUR! First boundary off the bat in this innings! A little too straight to end. Khawaja stylishly clips it through mid-wicket and the ball races away to the fence.
Another lovely delivery! This is on middle, it pitches and straightens once again. Khawaja looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Lovely, lovely stuff this! Once again angles this on off and gets it to shape away. Khawaja defends inside the line and gets beaten.
Slightly fuller again and on off, Khawaja guides it to the man at point.
Closer to the off pole this time but not close enough to make the batter play.
Fuller and outside off, Khawaja lets it be.
On a good length again around off, this is guided towards point.
One more delivery on a length and outside off, left alone.
This time gets the ball to come back in but the line is a little too wide outside off. Left alone.
Another one on a length and outside off, CB lets it be.
Good length again and outside off, this is left alone.
Another good delivery. This is on off and then straightens. Squares Bancroft up as he tries to defend.

That is a beauty! Not a lot you can do with that. From around the wicket, he angles it into the off pole and then gets it to leave the batter. Khawaja looks to push at it but gets beaten. End of a wonderful over by Broad.
Fuller and on off, Khawaja times it through covers. It does not go all the way but a couple results. UK is off the mark.
Back of a length on off, Khawaja guides it to point.
Good length and outside off, left alone. The crowd is right behind Broad at the moment.
Usman Khawaja is the new man in for the Aussies.

OUT! Knocked him over! Does not matter if the Warner nick was not appealed, there is no appeal needed here! Three in three for Broad against Warner in this series! Top class delivery and the crowd here is going bonkers. England are ecstatic. Early strike for them and another failure for Warner. Broad once again lands this on a length and around off, it jags back in and also skids through. Warner looks to defend but leaves a gap between bat and pad. The ball sneaks through and hits the top of leg. England would love another or maybe two more by Stumps.

What are we seeing here? Replays have rolled in for the ball on which Archer had beaten the outside edge of Warner's bat (3.4) but it seemed that he did not. However, there was a spike on Ultra Edge as the ball went past the bat and if the English team would have appealed or reviewed, Warner would have been back in the hut by now!
Back of a length on off, Bancroft pushes it towards cover.
The batsman goes after a wide one but misses.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the backfoot.
Beaten! Archer is bowling well here on his debut. Full again outside off, David tries to defend this one but the ball pitches and straightens and goes past the outside edge of Warner's blade.
Seems like a friendly warning from umpire Chris Gaffaney to Jofra Archer for running on the danger area. Nothing official.
Another full ball outside off, Warner plays it towards mid off.
Archer attacking the stumps now, he bowls this one fuller and around off pole. Bancroft blocks it out towards the covers and takes a single.
Length ball outside off, Bancroft lets it through to the keeper.
Another one angled into the batter, Warner defends it out.

Edged but short! Broad almost got Warner for the third time in a row! Fuller and around off, this one holds its length after pitching. Warner looks to push at it by staying rooted to his crease. The ball goes off the outside edge but short of second slip.
Leading edge but runs! This is fuller and into the pads, Warner is falling over as he tries to flick. It goes off the leading edge through covers for two.
This is angled into the batter, Warner works it to the man at square leg.
This is angled into the batter, Warner defends it onto the ground.
Good length and outside off, it has been left alone.
A solid push! Fuller and on off, Warner strokes it towards cover for one. Warner is off the mark. A testing over from Archer comes to an end.
A single! This is on middle, once again Archer gets it to jag back in. CB looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
Another one outside off, it has been left alone.
A good short one now! The batter ducks under it.

FOUR BYES! But what a delivery. This lands outside off and jags back in. Bancroft has a gap between bat and pad as he tries to defend. It sneaks through and keeps going away from Bairstow too who dives to his left but fails to stop it. A boundary.
Shorter and outside off, Bancroft lets it be.

Jofra Archer comes onto bowl. The last time he bowled at Lord's was the Super Over in the World Cup final and it was from this end. This though is a completely different challenge. He was brilliant with the white ball and I am very excited to see how he goes about with the red ball. Here he comes to bowl his first ball.
A dot to end! On middle, Warner keeps it out.
Another one on a fuller length outside off, Warner makes a leave.
Very short and way too wide outside off, Warner lets it be.
Fuller and around off, Warner drives it square on the off side but straight to point. Good confident shot that one.
Straightaway comes from around the wicket to Warner and lands it outside off, Warner makes a leave.
Australia and Bancroft are underway! Broad starts off with a very straight delivery, CB shuffles right across and works it through mid-wicket for one. Had he missed that, it would have been close.

Coming to the Aussie batsmen, how do they play this? Do they have the mental strength to see off the England bowlers? A score of 150/3 or 4 would look like a better reading but losing 10 wickets or more than 6 would really send a strong negative signal to the English team which will read - 'We are nothing without Smith.' An hour left to Tea. First aim to play this hour without losing any wicket. Stay tuned to check what happens.

The 90-run stand between Stokes and Buttler this morning literally killed Australia's hopes of going 2-0 up in this series. The visitors themselves looked deflated since morning and that news of Smith has already pegged them on the back foot. None of the bowlers were effective or impressive and Nathan Lyon endured a torrid third innings with the ball.

How the absence of one man can affect an entire team. Till yesterday evening, this English unit was thinking how to survive, how much target do they need to set for Australia with Smith and Warner in their unit, etc... etc... This morning, the very news of Smith being ruled out seems to have oozed in tons of confidence. The approach was positive and after Lunch, Stokes went berserk. The hosts were in a spot of bother at 71/4 but the big Ben played an innings of substance. Yes, he gave 2 catches in the span of 4 balls which were not taken by David Warner, but that is not his problem, is it?

So England declare with 50 overs remaining in the day. Remove another 2 overs for the changeover of the innings. Which means Australia have been given a target of 267 in 48 overs. Next to impossible. But can England pick up 10 wickets inside 48 overs? Very much a possibility. A longggg but exciting passage of play awaits us.

Good length ball on off, Jonny looks to drive it on the up to the off side but gets an inside edge which takes the ball to the on side and gets a single. 16 runs off the over and there is the declaration from Joe Root.
Short ball, Stokes pulls it towards square leg and gets just a single.
Length ball outside off, Stokes punches it through covers for a couple.

Very well fielded. Good length ball on off, Stokes pulls it wide of square leg. Wade in the deep runs to his left to clean it up. He gets wrong-footed as the ball spins in. Matthew Wade does really well to save it from going to the fence.
SIX! Hello, forget the whites, Stokes is making it look like T20. Fuller on middle, Stokes clears his front foot and heaves it over the square leg fence for a biggie.

FOUR! Don't know when the declaration is coming but Stokes is adding more to England's bucket. Low full toss on middle and leg, Stokes clears his front foot and smashes it straight down the ground through mid off for a boundary.

SIX! Bairstow going big now! Floated on middle and off, Bairstow takes his foot out of the way and slams it over mid-wicket for a biggie. Also with this six, Lyon has conceded over 100 runs in this innings itself without taking a wicket.
Defended off the front foot by Bairstow, presenting the full face of the bat.

There it is! Stokes completes his ton and is soaking in the applause from the crowd. This is on the leg side and Stokes just helps it down to fine leg and takes a single. Plays another superb innings at the home of cricket, taking England to a comfortable lead. 7th ton in Tests for Stokes and the second and Lord's.
Shorter this time, Stokes blocks this one out. Stokes making the world wait.
Full down the leg side, Stokes goes for the reverse sweep but misses.
Floated and on off, Stokes blocks this one out.
Nathan Lyon is back for another over. This might be the last over before the declaration comes in.
Good shot but no runs. Stokes on strike is all that matters. Full and outside off, JB drives it towards the cover fielder.
Length ball just on off, Bairstow tries to defend it but the ball takes an inside edge and then onto the pads.
Bairstow plays that off the front foot and into the ground.
Down the leg side, JB leaves it alone.
Quick double this time. Stokes has to wait. JB plays it towards point and takes off quickly, he completes the first one and then also takes the second one quickly as well. Tricky but will do.
Moves to 99, Stokes! He pushes this one towards covers and takes one.
Defended off the front foot by JB presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off length ball, Stokes guides this towards third man and takes a single as he inches closer to his ton.
FOUR! Short-arm jab by Stokes and he moves to 97 with that. On the pads was this one, Stokes goes onto the back foot and flicks it towards backward square leg for a boundary.
Shorter one this time and pulled away by Stokes towards mid-wicket. The batters take two runs.
Full and on off, JB pushes it towards covers and takes a single.
The batsman drives this through the covers.
FOUR LEG BYES! Down the leg side this time by Siddle, he looks to flick and misses. The ball goes through Paine as he fails to collect it and gives away four byes.
Bairstow pushes this fuller ball towards cover and rotates strike.

FOUR! Educational edge one must say. Good length ball on off, Bairstow goes back and opens the face of his bat to guide it towards third man. However, he gets a fine edge on it and the ball goes between the slip cordon and gully for a boundary towards third man.
Fuller this time, Bairstow pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Bairstow has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Length ball on middle and off, Bairstow tries to defend at it but gets an inside edge onto the pad.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Stokes gets on the back foot and cuts it towards covers for a boundary.
Length ball just outside off, defended by Stokes towards covers.
The ball has taken the inside edge of the bat of Stokes and goes down the leg side. The batters manage to come back for the second. 50-run stand comes up between the two in  very quick time here.

Ouch! That must have surely hurt. It is pitched on a length just outside off, the ball nips back in after pitching. Stokes goes for the drive straight down the ground but misses and is hit on the box. Stokes gets back up again quickly. Tough man!
Again goes for the shot to this ball outside off but misses.
Stokes has attempted to put bat on ball but fails.
Josh Hazlewood is back!
Good running! Guided down to fine leg by the batsman. They manage to come back for the second.
This time driven towards mid off, Khawaja dives towards his right and saves at least a run. Good fielding by him.
FOUR! Great shot through extra cover. Full ball outside off, Stokes gets into his stride and plays this one through extra cover for a boundary.
This time JB times it properly and takes a single off this one as he plays it towards mid-wicket.
Edged but safe! Full ball this time on the off pole, he looks to flick it towards mid-wicket but gets a leading edge. The ball floats towards covers but falls short of the fielder.
On a length just outside off, JB defends it off the back foot.
Peter Siddle is back.
SIX! Action replay! Again full and floated outside off, Stokes reminding us of the knock he played in the 2019 World Cup finals at this very same venue.
