SIX! Brilliant shot! Full, floated on off, Stokes gets down on one knee and slog sweeps it over the mid-wicket fence. He has waited to play this shot in this innings and now when he has connected he has connected it sweetly. Takes the lead over 200 in style.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Full and floated this time, Stokes goes for the drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes through gully towards third man for a couple.
Short and wide this time, cut to the point fielder.
Flat and on the off pole, Stokes defends it towards cover off the back foot.
Again on a length, blocked towards the cover fielder.
Good length on middle and off, tucked towards mid-wicket for one.
Superb pull shot by Bairstow here. Cummins goes short this time outside off, JB pulls it strongly towards mid-wicket but straight to the man. Single taken.
Length ball on the fifth stump line, pushed towards the cover fielder again.
This time on the off side similar length, Jonny pushes it towards the cover fielder.
Length ball on middle and leg, JB pushes it towards mid on off the back foot.
On the pads again, blocked towards mid-wicket.
On the leg side, Bairstow glances it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Defended off the back foot towards mid-wicket.
This time on the pads, Stokes flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Floated on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Flat and full on off, pushed back to Lyon.

Full on off, Bairstow drives it straight. Cummins gets his big boot on the way of the ball and it deflects it to mid on. Stokes at the non striker's end ends up falling as he anticipated the ball to come towards him. Ben provides us with some Matrix-esque dodge.
Length ball around off, Stokes strokes it towards point for one.
Full outside off, Ben swings his bat at it, going for the big one but misses.
Length ball on off, Ben gets on his back foot and blocks it.
Fuller on middle, Stokes strokes it to mid on.
Good length ball around off, Stokes punches it towards cover for a single.

Floated outside leg, Bairstow gets down on one knee and looks to play the paddle sweep. Tim Paine takes the ball and puts in a confident appeal. Aleem Dar is unmoved. Australia do not have any reviews left. It would have been wasted even if they had a review as the ball had indeed missed the bat which is later confirmed by Ultra Edge.

Flighted outside off, Stokes looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. The ball falls short and spins in after pitching. Labuschagne at second slip dives but gets beaten by the spin. The ball goes past him towards the third man fence. Three taken.
Now the reverse sweep. It is on middle, Jonny gets down on one knee and reverse sweeps it towards third man for one.
SIX! Brilliant shot! Tossed up on middle, Bairstow comes down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and smashes it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Floats one on off, Ben strokes it to cover and gets to the other end.
On the pads, Bairstow looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge towards the side of the pitch on the off side for one.
Good length ball around off, Stokes drives it wide of sweeper cover for a couple.
Fuller on off, Stokes keeps it out.
Outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
On the pads, Bairstow glances it fine down the leg side for a single.
Bouncer! Bairstow sits under it.
Good length ball on middle, Bairstow pushes it towards mid on.
Tossed up on off, Stokes keeps it out.

NOT OUT! Australia lose both their reviews. Floated delivery on middle and leg, Stokes looks to defend but misses and the ball hits him on the pads. There is a confident appeal from the Aussie players. Paine has a word with Lyon and then takes it upstairs. Replay rolls in and first confirms there is no bat involved. After some technical error our wait prolongs to see the Hawk Eye. After some laughs, Hawk Eye rolls in and it shows that the ball was missing the leg stump.

Australia have taken a review for LBW. Stokes is the man in question. The players are having a laugh in the middle as the Hawk Eye has some issues and the decision is on stand-by. Finally, the Hawk Eye comes in and shows that... MISSING LEG!

On the pads, Stokes looks to flick but the ball deflects off his pad fine down the leg side. There is a stifled appeal as the ball hits his thigh pad but the umpire is unmoved. The ball goes fine down the leg side and they take two leg byes.

Bairstow is off the mark with some help by the misfield. Tossed up on off, Bairstow strokes it to the right of mid off. Head there moves and dives to his right but fails to gather the ball. It deflects towards mid on and they take a single.
Play and miss! Floated outside off, Bairstow looks to drive but misses. Not an ideal start to the innings for Jonny.
On the pads, Stokes glances it to the on side for a single.
Jonny Bairstow walks out to the middle.

OUT! Caught! Buttler's patient innings comes to end. The short ball does the trick here and Cummins has ended this building stand. Cummins bangs it in short around the body. Buttler goes for the pull but gets a top edge on it. It goes high and straight to deep backward square leg. Hazlewood there hardly moves an inch and takes a simple catch. Soft dismissal for Buttler, he would be gutted to get out in such a fashion especially after taking his time out in the middle.
On a length around off, Buttler nudges it to point.
Length delivery on off, Ben strokes it to point and gets to the other end.
Short ball which rises just over the belly. It is down the leg side, Stokes goes for the pull but misses.

Excellent running, Good length ball on middle, Stokes tucks it with soft hands towards mid-wicket and immediately calls for two. The ball is to the left of the fielder and the duo of Buttler and Stokes is quick so they manage to get the second with ease.
Back of a length ball outside off, Stokes lets it carry to the keeper.
Shorter on top of off, Jos defends it to get through the over.
On the pads, Buttler glances it to mid-wicket with the spin.
Floated on the stumps, Buttler gets behind it and blocks it.
Excellent shot but straight to the man at cover. Flighted on off, Buttler drives it hard but cannot get it past the fielder at short cover.

That has spun leaps and bounds. It is pitched on the rough and spins away. Stokes looks to drive but misses. Paine too cannot gather it as the ball deflects off his gloves towards the third man region for one. They steal a bye.
Floated on off, Stokes keeps it out.
Nathan Lyon to continue from the other end.
Gets bat on ball for the first time in this session. Back of a length ball on off, Buttler gets on his toes and keeps it down.
On the fourth stump line and fuller in length. Jos offers no stroke.
Second bouncer of the over and it is also closer to the body. Buttler picks it early and ducks under it.
Fuller on the fifth stump line, Buttler leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler continues his cautious approach and leaves it alone.
Starts the new session with an unwelcoming bouncer. It is around middle and leg, Buttler sits under it.
We are back for the second session. Ben Stokes and Jos Buttler walk out to resume their innings. Pat Cummins to bowl the first over of the session.
... Day 5, Session 2 ...

So, do England go for the win and come out all guns blazing after Lunch (especially as they know that Steve Smith is not there for Australia) or do they play safely and drive this match towards a draw (which it already is)? Join us soon to find out!

LUNCH! Advantage England! Good session for England from all perspectives. The overnight batsmen who walked out to bat after the delay in play are still at the crease and continued the good momentum for them. It was expected that England would have come out aggressively but they just continued scoring around 3 runs per over. 21.4 overs bowled in this session, 61 runs scored and no wickets lost. Stokes has completed his 19th half ton of his Test career and looks to be going strong with Buttler who is on 31.
Flighted on off, Ben keeps it out to get to Lunch without any casualties.

In the air and just wide. Tossed up on middle, Buttler drives it uppishly as the ball sticks onto the surface. Luckily he pushes it way wide, to the right of the bowler. Lyon dives but cannot get close. The batsmen take a single as the  fielder from long on gathers it.
Floated around off, Buttler looks to defend but misses.
Floated outside off, Stokes looks to defend with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of a diving first slip for a single.
Floated on middle, Stokes defends it off the front foot.

WOW! That one has kept low and somehow managed to miss the stumps too. It is pitched on the rough outside off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball keeps very low and goes under Stokes' defensive bat on to the keeper.

FOUR LEG BYES! Length ball just outside the leg pole, Buttler looks to flick but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards the fine leg fence. Umpire Gaffaney waits for the Australian team to finish their decision on taking the LBW review and then signals leg byes.
Outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.
Good length ball this time, Buttler pushes it nicely towards the cover fielder.
Outside off, left alone by Buttler.
Length ball just outside off, Buttler walks a bit down the track and the ball hits the inside edge of his bat and onto the pads.
Flights one on off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes lets it go.
Floated on off, Buttler follows the boundary with a single towards cover.
FOUR! Creamed away! Floated on off, Buttler gets on his front foot and drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.

FIFTY FOR BEN STOKES! His 19th in Test cricket. He has continued his good form and once again when England were in trouble, Stokes raises his hands up and delivers. Short around off, Stokes cuts it to point and gets to his milestone. He raises his bat and soaks in all the applause.
Shorter on off, Stokes continues to defend Lyon of his back foot.
Length ball outside off, Stokes looks to push it towards covers. It takes the leading edge of his blade and the ball goes towards third man as the batters take one.
Comes down the track this time and Siddle pulls his length short. Stokes adjusts at the last moment and defends it out.
Length ball on middle and off, Stokes plays it back towards the bowler.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it down the leg side.
Length ball on middle and off pole, Stokes comes down the track and tries to hit the ball towards mid on. It takes the leading edge of his bat and the ball goes to point and the batters take two.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it towards cover.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it towards mid on and keeps the strike. The lead is now 150.
That ball has taken the inside edge of the batsman and thudded into his pads.
The ball pitches just outside the off pole and spins away, Stokes is beaten by the turn as he looks to defend.

This is pitched on the leg pole, it turns in and hits the pads of Buttler. It loops towards short leg and he dives to catch it but isn't able to do so. Leg bye taken as the ball rolls towards fine leg.
Full and tossed up outside off, Buttler blocks it out.
Flat and on the pads of Buttler, he blocks it out.
Fuller on middle and leg, defended towards the leg side by Stokes. Good start by Siddle.

Very well left from Stokes. Siddle comes steaming in and delivers a length ball around off, Stokes comes down the track and then shoulders arms to it. You seldom see that and this shows the confidence this man is carrying.
Well outside off, Stokes lets it be.
Beaten! Good length ball just outside off, Stokes looks to push at it but does so inside the line and misses.
This time a touch short, Stokes pushes it towards mid off.
Wide and full outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Peter Siddle back into the attack to bowl his first over of the day. 8-2-19-2 so far from him.

Excellent running. These two know each other well and that was visible here. Floated delivery on the pads, Stokes glances it towards fine leg. The fielder from square leg gives it a chase and pulls it back before the ropes. Stokes and Buttler are both quick between the wickets, they look for the third and get it with ease.
Shorter on the stumps, Stokes gets on his back foot and keeps it out.
Short around off, Stokes gets on his back foot and punches it to cover for one.
Tossed up on off, Ben keeps it out.
Flighted on the stumps, Stokes gets forward and defends it off the front foot.
Floated on middle, Stokes looks to defend but he does so off the inner half of his bat.
Length ball on the off pole, Buttler defends it off the back foot.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.

EDGED AND FOUR! Buttler gets lucky on this one. Pitched full and on off, Buttler goes for a cover drive but gets a thick outside edge as the ball goes between gully and the slip cordon to the third man fence.
Length ball just outside off, Stokes pulls it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
Length ball just outside off, pushed back towards the bowler. Hazlewood bends and tries to get a hand to it but fails to do so as the ball goes towards mid on.

FOUR! MAJESTIC! All of a sudden, England are playing with renewed vigour. Full and around middle, Stokes drives this straight back. Hazlewood tries stopping it with his right hand, putting half a bend, but the ball whizzes past. The lead is 140 now.
Length ball just outside off, pushed to point off the back foot.
Full and floated, Buttler pushes it back to the bowler.
Flat on off and middle, goes towards the off side off the outside half of the bat.
Full and tossed up on middle and leg, pushed back to Lyon.
FOUR! Full and tossed up outside off, Buttler leans into the drive and caresses the ball through the cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle and off, Stokes pushes it with soft hands towards covers and takes a single.
Bouncer to end the over, Buttler ducks under it and the ball goes to Tim Paine behind the stumps.
Length ball just outside off, Buttler pushes it towards the point fielder.
Again outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Full and on the pads of Buttler, he flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and the batters take a couple.
Length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.

Short length ball on the leg pole, Stokes pulls it towards square leg for a single. 50-run stand up between Stokes and Buttler. This stand has tilted the match back in the balance. England will be looking to get a move on from here on if they want to stand any chance of winning this match.
11.4 overs have been bowled today and England still have 6 wickets intact with Stokes and Buttler going strong. The match seems to be heading back in the balance and maybe towards a draw too.
Tossed up away from the off stump, Buttler leaves it alone.
Flighted outside off, Buttler looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto his body.
Floated on off, Buttler looks to drive but it goes to the on side off the inner half of his blade.
Flighted around off, Buttler drives it through point and gets a couple to take the partnership to 49.
Tossed up around off, Jos gets on his front foot and keeps it out.
Shorter around off, Buttler nudges it to mid-wicket.
Fuller on middle, Stokes comes down the track and taps it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Nicely bowled. Hazlewood hits the deck hard around off, Stokes looks to defend it inside the line and the away movement sees the ball go to the keeper.
Length ball around off, Buttler stands tall and punches it wide of cover for one.
Back of a length ball on off, JB defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Jaffa to end the over. This is pitched around off and turns in sharply. Stokes looks to defend but misses and the ball goes onto hit the thigh pad of Stokes.
Once again on the pads, Ben tucks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, BS flicks it to the on side.
Shorter on off, Stokes keeps it out.

EDGED AND FOUR! That was not far away from Warner at first slip. Tossed up outside off, Stokes falls in the honey trap to drive. The ball turns away and finds the thick outside edge of Ben's willow. It flies to the left of Warner at first slip who dives but it goes wide of him and to the third man fence for a boundary.
Shorter around off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Buttler defends it off the front foot to get through the over.
This one keeps low, something similar in the first Test was the undoing for Buttler. This time Jos keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it late.
Length ball on top of middle, Stokes just helps it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Beaten! Stokes tries to play at this ball outside off but fails.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

NOT OUT! Inside edge detected by the Ultra Edge! Waste of a review by the Australian team. This is a good length ball, seems to be pitching outside leg. The ball hits the inside edge of Stokes' bat and then onto the pads. However, the Australians gambled on this one and thought that the ball hit the pads directly. They think about it and go for the review at the last second. The replays roll in and the Ultra Edge shows that the ball has hit the bat first. Stokes survives. Also, the Hawk Eye comes in later and shows that the ball pitched outside leg. Had it not hit the bat of Stokes, he was still safe. Australia lose one of their reviews.
Just at the last moment, Paine signals the 'T' to take a referral for LBW. Looks like a tough decision as the bat seems to be hitting the ball and pad at the same time.
Josh Hazlewood is into the attack for the first time today.
Loopy ball on off, JB defends it to get through the over.
Floats one on the pads, Buttler glances it to the on side.
Flighted outside off, Buttler looks to drive it to the off side but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Buttler tucks it to short leg.
Off spinner on off, Buttler glances it to short leg.
Short around off, Stokes hangs back on his back foot and punches it to sweeper cover for one.
Length ball outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Short ball down the leg side, it does not raise as much. Buttler though ducks under it. Paine dives to his left and takes a good carry.
Fuller on off, Buttler blocks it off the front foot.

Appeal for LBW but turned down. Full on middle and leg, Buttler looks to flick but misses. The ball hits him flush on the pads. There is an appeal from the Australian players but nothing from the umpire. It looked to be going down the leg and hence no review. Smart bowling this though, outside off, outside off and then one on the stumps.
Outside off and once again Jos is not interested.
Good length ball outside off, Cummins wants Buttler to go for a drive but Jos says no and leaves it.
Shorter on off, BS keeps it out.
Follows it up with a calm back foot defense.

FOUR! Well placed and very well timed. Tossed up on off, Stokes just times it wide of mid on. He does not use power but just pure timing. Hazlewood gives it a chase from mid on and puts in a dive to pull it back but he fails in his attempt to do so.
Tossed up on off and middle, Ben strokes it to mid on.

BREAKING NEWS - Marnus Labuschagne has been approved by the ICC as an active player as he replaces Steve Smith and thus, he becomes the first ever concussion substitute made in cricketing history. Apparently, Smith reported grogginess and a headache this morning and his response to concussion testing had deteriorated. His availability for the Leeds Test now could be doubtful as players cannot participate in training for at least 6 days.
Flatter on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Shorter on off, Stokes gets on his back foot and defends it onto the ground.
Length ball around off, Buttler defends it towards cover-point to get through the over unscathed. Maiden for Pat.
Good length ball outside off, Jos has nothing to do with it.
Cummins maintains his off stump line to Buttler. This is served full, Jos defends it to the left of mid off.
Fuller on off, Jos Buttler pushes it to cover.
On a length very close to the off pole, Buttler keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it.
Good length ball around off, Buttler defends it towards point.
Shorter on off, Ben calmly defends it to get through the over.
Arm ball outside off, Ben gets on his front foot and leaves it alone.
Off spinner pitching on off, Buttler glances it with the spin towards fine leg for a single.
Slightly short and turning in, Buttler defends it off the back foot towards cover against the spin.
Flighted on off, Buttler blocks it out.
Tossed up on off, Buttler defends it off the front foot.
On the fourth stump line, Stokes does not tease that one.
Not much swing on this one, it is outside off and calmly left.
Peach of a delivery! Length ball on the fourth stump line, it nips back in a lot after pitching. Stokes though shows his awareness and leaves it alone. The ball just about misses his front pad.

FOUR! This is right off the meat. Brutal hitting. Good length ball outside off, Stokes picks the length early and flat-bats it wide of short cover. Wade there does not even move as he had little to no time to react. The ball goes wide and over him to the fence.

EDGED AND FOUR! Nicely bowled this by Cummins. He bowls a pacy full ball outside off, tempting Stokes to drive. He obliges but gets a thick outside edge. It flies to the right of gully, Khawaja there dives on that side but cannot get his hand to it. The ball races away to the third man fence for a boundary.
Good length ball on top of middle and off, Stokes gets on his back foot and defends it.
Flatter and quicker on middle and leg, Stokes looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards square leg for a single. Stokes will keep the strike.
Sharp spin on this one. It is pitched on off and spins away, Stokes defends it towards cover with the spin.
Floated outside off, Ben shoulders arms to his one.
Slightly shorter on off and middle, Stokes defends off the back foot.
Flighted outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
First run of the day. Off spinner on off, Buttler turns it behind square on the leg side with the spin and gets a single.
Nathan Lyon to partner Cummins from the other end.
Length ball outside off, Stokes once again has a slash but misses. One of the biggest overs this as it started on Day 4 and ended on Day 5 after an hour's delay.
Bounce and swing on this one. Good length ball outside off, Stokes covers his off stump and leaves it alone. There is late inswing on this one. Paine takes it around his head towards his right.
Back of a length and outside off, Stokes leaves it alone.
Play and a miss to begin the day. Cummins steams in and hits the deck hard outside off, Stokes has a slash at it but misses.

We are all set to begin. Isa Guha to ring the bell. Pat Cummins to resume the proceedings for Australia on Day 5. Ben Stokes and Jos Buttler step out onto the pitch for England. 2 slips and a gully in place. We also have some news on Steve Smith. He is ruled out of this match and the third Test match as well due to a concussion suffered yesterday. Marnus Labuschagne replaces him in the field. Here we go...
Update 1145 local (1045 GMT) - The rain has gone... for now at least, the inspection is done and we are all set to start at 1210 local. 88 overs to be bowled today.
Update 1126 Local (1026 GMT) - Finally we have a good news! The rain has stopped and the covers are coming off too. There will be an inspection at 1140 local.

We are all ready to begin. Oops... this is what happens when you write the same thing every day. WE ARE NOT READY TO BEGIN. It is raining in London and we are not going to have a start on time. So, on an already extended day, we will be having a delayed start. There is water on the covers and puddles on the outfield. We might need at least an hour before we begin. But first, the rain needs to stop.

Now, the second chain of thought. It is overcast today. Do you risk your bowlers and fielders by declaring? Thanks to a damp outfield, it might be slippery as well. Wouldn't it be better if you just keep batting and batting and batting and tire the Aussies out? The next Test is just 3 days away.

How is Steve Smith? That is the first and only question. He was pummeled down (in the literal meaning) by his Indian T20 league mate, Jofra Archer and his resilience to come back and fight was the talk of the town. England will believe that he may not be the same old self and will back themselves to get Australia all out quickly.

Welcome to our coverage of Day 5 of the 2nd Ashes Test! As it stands, the match is slightly in the favor of the visitors with England reeling at 96/4. The hosts lead by 104 runs. Are they thinking of a win? If they are, they will have to score some quick runs and then look to bundle Australia out. Also, in the search of quick runs, they might lose wickets and that would mean Australia will have an upper hand. As long as the visitors are concerned, they would not want to chase anything over 200. And for that to happen, the bowlers need to strike early in the first session.
... Day 5, Session 1 ...
Day 5. 98 overs. Four results possible. What will happen? Who will win? Will anyone win? Join us at 11  am local (1000 GMT) for all the action from the Sunday drama. ADIOS! TAKE CARE!

Australia have got a small carrot dangling in front of them. They have a slim chance of winning but for that, they will need to bowl England out before the lead crosses 150. Once the 150-mark is breached, the tourists' batting, which has been under the scanner as well, might find itself under severe pressure.

It will be interesting to see how England play this. Do they be proactive and score quickly, declaring at a time which is enough for their bowlers to take 10 wickets? Or do they just bat and bat and bat and make Australia toil? Remember, the next Test is on 22nd August, so they will make sure that the visitors do not recover in time.

Saturday started with Australia tantalizingly poised on 80/4, but Steve Smith and the lower order bailed the team out of trouble. The former skipper took a lot of blows on his body and the neck, left the ground being retired hurt but then came back to battle hard. If Australia do get to bat on Sunday, he will be definitely needed and the fact that he has been ruled out of any fracture on his arm or concussion comes as massive relief to Australia.

What a day of cricket. 89.4 overs, 266 runs, 10 wickets. When Australia batted out 2 sessions, it seemed like there is nothing else but a draw left in this game. But England's mini collapse has got the match open once again. 98 overs. Two nervous teams. A riveting Day 5 awaits us.
Defended off the back foot by Stokes and it looks like the heavens have opened up as well. That's it! STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Length ball outside off, Stokes lets it be. It seems that the English players are trying every way possible to waste some time as we see Ben Stokes tapping the pitch before the start of the over.
Again outside off, Buttler lets it go. Maiden by Josh but the Australians need a wicket here so that they can end the day on a good note.
Finally Hazlewood attacks the stumps, it pitches on a good length on off. Jos blocks it out.
Fuller this time, the ball pitches and moves away from Jos.
Again a length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone by Buttler.
Fullish just outside off pole, Buttler pushes it to the cover fielder.
Josh Hazlewood returns. 6-0-15-0 so far.
Outside off this time from Cummins, Stokes lets it be.
FOUR! On the pads from Cummins as Stokes works it fine down the leg side to get a four.
Good shot that but finds the fielder in the mid off region.
Beaten! Swing and miss from Stokes. This is not needed right now with just a few overs left for the day. Wide outside off, Stokes again goes hard at the ball, gets beaten.
Full on middle this time, Stokes works it nicely towards mid-wicket and run a couple.
Shortish one outside off, Stokes looks to power this through cover but mistimes it onto the pitch.
Around off, solidly defended.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
This one darts in after pitching on the rough, Ben looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
How did that miss the off stump? Full and outside off, just missing the rough, Stokes lets it go and the ball goes straight on, just missing the off stick by inches!
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
Wide outside off on fifth stump, Buttler left it alone.
Fullish one on middle and leg, Buttler works this towards mid-wicket and take a couple.
FOUR LEG BYES! Poor one now! Pitches this on middle and leg and seamed further down the leg side. Buttler misses his flick but the ball kisses the pads and go fine for a boundary.
Beaten! Gets the batsman to play by pitching the ball closer to the off stump, it straightened a bit as it came closer to the bat. Buttler was lucky not to edge that one.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Buttler pushes it towards mid on.
Fullish ball on fourth stump line, Buttler blocks it off his front foot.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flicks this towards mid-wicket for a run.
Down the leg side, tucked towards fine leg for a single.
Full and around middle, blocked watchfully.
Outside off, punched back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, nudged through fine leg. Pat Cummins races all the way from deep backward square leg and dives to his right to stop the ball. Three runs taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Now an inside edge. A length ball, around middle, BS looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads off an inside edge.
A length ball, down the leg side, Ben looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads. He is searching for the ball and then gets back in his crease.
Walks into the shot and pushes this towards mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length around middle and leg, Stokes lets it go on length and it goes over his stumps.
Pat Cummins is back on. 5-1-8-2 so far.
Around off, pushed towards point.
Floated, around middle, solidly blocked towards cover.
Around middle, pushed towards the bowler.
Tossed up, outside off, driven to the left of Josh Hazlewood at mid off.
Full and outside off, Jos drives this through the covers but Travis Head dives to his right and makes an excellent stop.
Outside off, spinning in, Buttler looks to cut but gets a bottom edge onto his pads.
Walks down the track and defends.
Outside off, angling away, left alone.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers for a run.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
A length ball outside off, watchfully defended.
MORE LUCK! A length ball, down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but gets a leading edge which balloons over square leg! A single taken.
Buttler taps this good length ball on the off side comfortably.
Works this towards fine leg to take a run.
Another one that lands on the rough and goes away from the batsman, Stokes does nothing.

Good length ball on leg, Stokes looks to punch through mid-wicket but is hit on the pads. That looked going down the leg side but surprisingly Hawk Eye suggests it was hitting the leg pole. No reviews from Australia.
That spit off the surface. Pitched on the rough on off and went high in the gloves of Paine.
Full on off, Stokes lunges to block it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.

LEADING EDGE, RUN OUT CHANCE, BOTH SAFE! Ohhh... things are happening. Full and outside off, swinging in, Buttler looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge and goes over Siddle. Stokes looks for the single but Buttler is busy searching for the ball. Stokes has to turn and meanwhile mid on gets across and has a throw at the bowler's end but it is pretty wide! The big Ben dives in.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball just outside off, it pitches and nips away from him. Buttler is beaten by the away movement on the ball.
Short and outside off, Buttler leaves it alone. The ball swung way too much after the ball went past Buttler and Paine dives to his right to grab it.
Full ball on off, pushed to mid off by Buttler.
Full and outside off, Stokes pushes this towards mid off.
Shorter this time and on off, Stokes goes on the back foot and blocks it out.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes leaves the ball alone.

What are you doing, Buttler? Dances down the track to this middle and leg good length ball but misses the flick and is hit on the pad. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters cross ends. Lucky there that he got a tickle on the pads or he would've been stumped.
Slightly fuller again, Buttler blocks it well towards point.
Fuller ball outside off, Butter looks to work it around off side but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Stokes lets the ball go outside his off stump.

This time fuller on the pads of Buttler, he flicks it nonchalantly towards mid-wicket. Head there dives to his right and gets some hand on it, slowing the pace down. He gets up and runs back and the batters take three in the meantime.
Fuller this time around off, Buttler blocks it out.
First ball faced by Buttler, he leaves it alone.
Jos Buttler walks in with his side in tatters.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siddle gets another one and in a surprising turn of events, it is Australia who are now on top. Siddle pitches this one on the leg pole on a length. The ball pitches and drifts away from Burns. He tries to defend at it off the front foot but gets a fine outside edge on it and Paine takes an easy catch behind the wickets. Australia jump with joy and England in deep trouble here. England effectively here 79/4.
Full on middle and leg, Burns pushes this back to Siddle.

EDGED, DROPPED! David Warner again. Full and around off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball spins off the rough, takes the outside edge and flies to Warner at first slip. He has actually moved a step closer to Paine and hence has to dive to his left to take the catch. Had he stayed at his original position, he would have gobbled it. He is furious with himself. What an over from Lyon.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Close! Outside off, Ben looks to cut but almost misses. Gets a bottom edge towards point.

EDGED, FOUR! Late reaction from Warner. Full and around middle, Stokes looks to defend but gets squared up. Warner initially moves to his left at slip, then goes to his right but the extra second costs him. The ball goes past his right hand behind, to the third man fence.
Outside off, looks to cut, does Stokes but he gets an under edge which bounces between Tim Paine's legs behind. Two runs taken.
Short to start. Outside off, Burns cuts it through the covers for a single.
No surprise. Two left-handers at the crease and the skipper says that I want my spinner bowling. 19-2-67-3 for Lyon so far.
Outside off, Stokes lets this one be.
Ben Stokes walks in next, at number 5, replacing Denly. An hour to go to Stumps, weather permitting.

OUT! Caught and bowled! Siddle gets Denly and England are three down now. Siddle bowls this one on a good length just outside off, he rolls his finger on it and the ball gets slow off the pitch as a result. Denly is early into his shot and the ball goes uppishly towards Siddle and he makes no mistake in taking the catch with both his hands. England 3 down with just 64 runs on the board (Lead by 72).
FOUR! Full and on the pads of Denly, he just rotates his wrists and plays a classy flick towards the mid-wicket fence.
Full ball on middle and off, Rory tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

Full and outside off, Denly looks to drive but the ball scoots off the outside edge past gully towards third man. Three runs taken. 50-RUN STAND IS UP! Consecutive ones for these two. They added 66 in the first innings.
A short ball wide outside off, left alone.

Short ball this time by Hazlewood, Denly goes for the risky pull and top edges it. Luckily, the ball falls short of Travis Head at mid-wicket and the batters cross ends. No need for Denly to play such shots.
Short and outside off, Denly looks to cut but misses out on it. Could have resulted in some runs here.
On the pads of Denly, he tucks it towards mid-wicket.
The ground staff is getting ready. A light drizzle is falling, actually. The umbrellas are slowly going up in the stands.
Length ball just outside off, Denly guides it towards the point fielder.
Good length ball just outside off, played towards the cover fielder.
Full ball on the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards backward square leg and rotates the strike.
Josh Hazlewood time. 5-0-13-0 so far.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Siddle produces an outside edge by pitching this on middle and off on a good length. The ball flies between slip and gully for a boundary. No luck for Siddle as yet.
Fullish ball on off and middle, Denly looks to drive this but gets an inside edge which hits the pad. There's an appeal but a mild one.
FOUR BYES! Poor stuff this from Siddle. Another one going down the leg side. Denly missed his flick there. Paine dives to his left to stop that but it is too far from him. 50 up for Australia.
Misses his line this time. Pitches this on middle and the ball goes further down towards Paine as Denly misses the flick.
Slightly shorter around off, Denly taps it towards gully.
DRINKS BREAK. Australia's period for sure, but it could have been so much better. Burns' LBW not reviewed while Denly's catch put down. England are effectively 54/2 but they could have been 40/4.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Short ball and on middle and leg, Denly pulls this towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

Run out chance! Safe! More luck for England. Denly pushes this full ball towards mid on and sets off for a single. However, Burns is caught ball-watching and does not even take a start. Denly is almost within handshaking distance with his partner but has to stop. He now turns to go back and luckily for him, Usman Khawaja at mid on is slow to throw it to the keeper's end. Denly manages to get back in time. England living dangerously here. Burns should concentrate more on trusting his partner rather than watch the ball.
FOUR! Great shot dancing down the track by Denly. Lyon tosses it up on middle and leg, Joe comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up full and on leg, pushed to mid on.
Tossed up just outside off, the ball pitches and moves away from Denly. He misses as he defends inside the line. Even Paine behind the stumps is not able to collect this one.
A bumper but Siddle has got the direction wrong. Going down leg and too high. Burns ducks under it.
This is slightly fuller, Burns pats it towards point.
Outside off again on a good length, Burns leaves it alone.
Beaten but a no ball! Siddle oversteps there. This was in the channel outside off, Burns wanted to smash this but is beaten.
Shortish one on off, Burns taps this towards the off side.
Fuller ball on the stumps, Denly looked to flick this hard but is beaten to get hit on the pads. Ooohs and aaahs there but this was going down. Went to fine leg as the batsman change ends.
Good length outside off, Denly leans and blocks it towards point.
The batsman gives this a full swing of the bat, and connects. They manage to come back for the second.

Loud appeal by the Aussies for LBW but umpire Aleem Dar turns it down. Lyon bowls this one shorter and on middle and off. It goes in with the angle and hits Burns on the front pad as he misses to defend it. The Aussies appeal in unison but the umpire shakes his head. They think about going for the review but ultimately decide against it. The replays roll in, Hawk Eye comes into play and it shows THREE REDS! This could well prove to be a turning point in this match.
FOUR! Shorter than the last one and outside off, this time Burns makes full use of it and cuts it towards covers for a boundary.
This one short and outside off, Burns goes onto the back foot and guides it towards third man. Cummins there misfields and allows the batters to take two.
Floated on leg, Denly nudges it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Tossed up outside off, Denly takes a stride forward and tries to play it towards the on side. It hits his pads as he misses the flick and the ball goes to Warner at first slip.
Fuller in length outside off, Burns punches it to cover.
Beaten this time! Good bowling from Siddle as he is consistently bowling in that channel outside off.
On the middle and leg line, Burns works it towards fine leg.
Blocks this outside off ball off his front foot.
Shortish one this time on middle, Denly works it towards mid on to take a run.

DROPPED! David Warner, of all the people. Unlucky is now becoming the nickname of Siddle. Super ball in the channel outside off, on a length. Denly has a poke with hard hands and gets an outside edge which flies to David Warner at first slip. He goes to his right slightly slowly as the ball dips but can't hold on that one. A missed opportunity there.
Short and outside off, Burns gets an under edge onto it and the ball goes very low near the keeper. It goes behind him and Warner from first slip mops it up.
Again tossed up and on the pads, Lyon pushes this one towards mid-wicket and crosses ends.
Full and on the legs, pushed towards mid on.
On the pads this time, Burns flicks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
FOUR! Too short and Burns punishes Lyon as he rocks onto the back foot and cuts this through point for a boundary.
Flat and way outside off, the ball pitches and turns away. Burns plays an awkward cut but straight to the cover fielder.
Spin time! Very early in this innings as Lyon comes to roll his arms.
Fuller on middle and off, pushed to mid off, maiden by Siddle.
Length ball outside off, Denly shoulders arms to it.
Outside off again, Denly leaves it alone.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

Woah! What happened on this ball? Did it come off the crack on the surface? It pitched on a length and swung in quickly. The ball hit Denly's inside edge and then onto the box. Awkward scenes out here.
Length ball on off pole, Denly defends it.
First bowling change of the innings. Peter Siddle replaces Pat Cummins.
On the hips, Denly glances this one towards backward square leg and keeps the strike.
Another one on the pads, this time to Burns. He also flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
On the pads of Denly, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Outside off, Denly leaves this one alone.
Ouch! That must have hurt Denly. The ball shoots up after pitching on middle, Joe tries to block it out but the ball hits his glove and then his stomach. He looks a bit rocked by it.
Good length delivery outside off, Denly lets it be.
Length ball just outside off, Rory pushes it towards mid off. 2 runs off the over.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Bouncer this one outside off, Burns ducks under it.
Fuller this time outside off, Burns tries to block it out but the ball goes to gully off the outer half of his bat.
Length ball on middle and leg, Burns pushes it towards mid on.
Outside off on a length, Burns pushes this towards the cover fielder.
Good fuller ball on off, Denly walks across a bit to push it off the front foot.
Good length ball on middle, Denly works it towards the leg side.
Fuller on off, Denly defends it well.
Bouncer again but outside off, Burns converge to pull but drags this towards square leg to take a run.
Shortish one outside off, taps it off the back foot towards the off side.
Bouncer on the hips down the leg side, Burns looked to work it around but is hit on body. No run taken there.
Fuller on the legs, Denly pushes this towards mid-wicket.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

On the hips of Denly, he looks to flick but misses his shot. It hits the thigh pad and the ball rolls towards backward square leg as Hazlewood there collects it. While collecting the ball, Hazlewood fell down almost doing a split. He quickly gets up and the batters take two in the meantime.
FOUR! Short ball down the leg side this time by Cummins, Denly trying to keep it down gets a glove on this one and the ball races towards the fine leg fence.
Good length ball on off again, Denly gets the inner half of his bat on it and the ball rolls towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Denly.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Burns works it towards mid-wicket. They take a couple.
Another short ball, Burns evades this nicely.

IN THE AIR... SAFE! Shortish ball on the body, Burns looks to defend but the ball lobs towards Usman Khawaja at gully who is late to react as the ball drops very close to him. He got out similarly in the 2nd innings of last Test.
News is coming out that Steve Smith has gone to the hospital for a precautionary x-ray on his left elbow. He was hit by a Jofra Archer delivery over there as well.
Good length outside off, came in after passing the batsman. A good leave from Burns though.
Short ball on middle this time, Burns ducks under it nicely.
Good length on off, Rory taps it on the off side.
Outside off, on a length, JD looks to defend but the ball comes in a long way and beats the inside edge! Top over from Cummins. A DOUBLE WICKET MAIDEN!
Another leave outside off.
Outside off, in the avenue of apprehension, left alone.
No hat-trick for Cummins. A length ball outside off, coming in a long way, Denly misses his tuck and is hit on the pads.
The next batsman in for England is Joe Denly. England in a spot of bother here and Pat Cummins is on a hat-trick!

OUT! Caught! Massive blow for England. What a delivery first up to the England captain. Cummins is again in the channel for the right-hander. Root is new to the crease and wants to feel the first ball as he pokes at it and gets a thick edge to skipper Paine who is not going to miss out on that. Body blow this one. Australians smelling blood now.
Skipper Root walks in.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Cummins takes the first wicket of this English innings and Roy is dismissed for a paltry score of 2 runs. Cummins bowls this one short and on the body of Roy, he looks to flick it towards fine leg but gets a top edge on it. The ball loops behind Cummins and he runs back and catches it. Jubilation for Australia as Roy is out of here and England are 1 down for just 9 runs.
This time in the channel of uncertainty to the left-hander. Rory knows his off stump and leaves it alone.
Too high! Pitched short on middle and off but this goes high again.
Shortish ball on middle and leg, Roy works it towards fine leg to get off strike.
Edged but didn't carry! This again is in the channel outside off. Roy has a poke at this without any feet movement. Gets an outside edge but the ball doesn't carry to the second slip fielder.
Shortish but wide outside off, Roy is not lured at that one.
Shortish length on middle and off, comes in with the angle to hit on the stomach as Roy misses his flick.
Beaten! Good delivery in the channel outside off. Burns looks to push and is beaten all ends up. Good end to the over from Cummins.
Bumper this time to the left-hander but the line is down the leg side and it is too high, Rory ducks under it.
Shortish one, rising a bit but Roy works it nicely through deep backward square leg for one. Roy off the mark with that single.
Fuller ball around off, Roy blocks it solidly.
Shortish around the fourth stump line, Roy blunts it close to the body off his back foot.
Cummins pitches this on middle and off and the ball goes further away as Roy misses his flick.
Down the leg side again, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Fuller this time but on middle and leg, Rory flicks it in the gap between mid on and mid-wicket and takes a couple.
Bouncer this time, Rory does well to evade it.
Length ball outside off, Burns lets it go.
Good defense off the back foot on this length ball outside off.
FOUR! Length ball just outside off, Burns stands tall and punches this off the back foot towards the cover fence. Lyon gives it a chase but sloppily lets it go through for a boundary.
Josh Hazlewood to share the new-ball attack with Cummins.
Length ball outside off, stays a touch low, Roy looks to defend but the ball stays low and goes off the bottom edge towards mid off.
A length ball outside off, JR pushes this watchfully towards the slip cordon.
A length ball around off, Jason taps this awkwardly to the off side.
A length ball, around off, Roy gets squared up a touch and pushed it towards short mid-wicket.
Off the mark. A length ball, tucked past short leg for a single.
Right on target immediately. A length ball, around off, left alone.

That is all we have from this 5-day-cum-4-day match. Australia manage to cling on to the urn and series lead but one will believe that with Smith potentially ruled out of the next Test, England have the momentum and the arsenal to level the series. But then, Australia had the momentum coming into this one. Probably it will be best if we leave it to the players to get us a wonderful game of cricket. Join us on Thursday, 22nd August, 2019 at 11 am local (1000 GMT) for all the action from the third Test at Headingley, Leeds. ADIOS! TAKE CARE!
BEN STOKES HAS BEEN NAMED THE MAN OF THE MATCH. It was his century which brought the game to life. England will hope that it spurs him on for the rest of the series.

Coming to the bowling. Two bowlers who were playing their first Test in this series - Josh Hazlewood and Jofra Archer - the latter playing his debut Test - lit up the Lord's. Hazlewood rocked up England's top order while Jofra Archer went for the head of every batsman. He kept reminding us of the fiery Caribbean pace of the 70s and 80s, hitting the Aussies hard and making them hop around like rabbits. Regardless of this result, one just feels that the Ashes has just begun for the English. Archer is probably the difference between the two sides and with 3 games to go, this series is waiting for a turnaround.

In cricket, they say that nothing is over till it is really over. Joe Root took a controversial catch to dismiss Marnus Labuschagne and the game turned. Next over, Matthew Wade was dismissed. 3 overs later, Paine threw his wicket away. Boy, the game was truly alive and kicking. But Cummins and Travis with a cool head managed to see off the remaining nervous moments and ensured that the Aussies still stay in the series lead.

Normally, with 10 wickets to play out 48 overs, you do expect the batting side to see those off. But Australia were reeling even before the first ball was bowled, as Smith was not there. They were reduced to 19/2 and then 47/3 before Marnus Labuschagne and Travis Head staged a 85-run stand and almost saw the team home to stuff out a draw. ALMOST.

England were rocked early in their second innings as well, being reduced to 71/4 but then lives given to Ben Stokes - twice in 4 balls by David Warner let them off the hook. The scenario changed this morning when it was announced that Smith will miss the rest of this Test match. A new vigour came into the hosts' camp. They pummeled the bowling to all parts, with Stokes raising a century to remember.

That fourth day saw a lot of action. Steve Smith taking matters into his own hands and then that contest between him and Jofra Archer. Hit on the elbow, hit on the neck, felled over, concussed and eventually retiring hurt, before coming back on. He has been ruled out of the next Test as well but that is for now. What if he says he is fit on the 21st?

This Test match had all the ingredients. Rain robbed us off 5 sessions. Out of a potential 15. But in the 10 that we got, fantastic cricket was played. Australia's decision to bowl first surprised all, but their bowling unit got that in their favour by dismissing England for 258. But their own batting could not come to terms again and fell 8 runs short.

Well, umpire Aleem Dar takes the bails off. Australia have 4 wickets left, 3 balls left in the day and the time has ticked past 7.24 pm local time, which was the last permissible limit till when play could have gone on. Root walks over solemnly and shakes hands with Cummins. The second Test ends in a draw. We go 1-0 into Leeds.
Full and around off, Cummins lunges to smother the spin.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and around off, watchfully defended past short leg.

Fullish ball on off, Head drives it firmly through covers. The ball was going towards the fence but no one runs. Why would Head not take a single? As fate would have it, the ball stops near the ropes as Broad hares after it. That means Cummins would face the next over. Poor thinking from Head.
Another fullish ball from Leach which doesn't land on the rough. Head blunts it nicely.
Another fullish ball outside off, Head punches it towards mid off to get a couple.
Blocks it from the crease to this fullish ball.
Beaten this time! Fullish ball on fourth stump line. Head has a poke at it but is beaten.
Fullish ball on off, Head drives it straight to cover.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman has offered no stroke to an incoming delivery.

NOT OUT. Missing off. Review in excitement and desperation. Pitched around leg, from over the wicket, Cummins pads it away. He is hit on the pads and Leach appeals. Root immediately goes for the review. Ball Tracker confirms that it was spinning away.
Root has gone for a review! Did the ball do enough to come back in? Cummins did not offer any shot. Here comes Ball Tracker. Missing off. Reviews done and dusted for England.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
WAS THAT A CATCH? Probably. Full and outside off, Cummins comes forward to drive and almost spoons a catch to Rory Burns at silly point. Burns dives but cannot hang on!
Head blocks this well again to see off the over.
Fuller one on off again, Head pushes this to the cover fielder again.
Good shot but straight to the fielder. Fullish on off, timed it straight to the cover fielder.
Fullish one this time, taps it to the slip fielder.
Blocks this fullish ball from the crease.
Starts with one outside off on a fullish length which lands on the rough, Head looks play at it but is hit on the pads.

Interesting. The umpires feel that it is too dark right now. They reckon that Jofra Archer cannot bowl as his pace is too quick for the batsmen under this light. It has to be spin and Joe Denly it is to bowl.
Fuller this time, Cummins blocks it well to see off the over. 4 more overs to go.
Another good length ball to which Cummins blocks off his front foot.
Left that ball outside off.
Lunges and blocks this by coming forward.
Good length ball outside off, Cummins pushes this one towards gully.
Fullish one on the middle from Leach, Cummins blocks it well.
Another bumper on the hips from Archer. Head looks to work it down the leg side but is hit on the hands.
Another back of length ball on middle and leg, Head pushed it towards the fine leg fielder.
What was that? Shortish one outside off, Head looked to sway away at first but eventually played at it to get beaten.
Another bouncer! What a spell this is from Archer. This is on middle and off, Head leaps in the air to block this one to the point fielder.

In the air... just short! A length ball down the leg side, Cummins nudges it towards leg gully. Ben Stokes comes charging in but the ball lands in front of him. He is unable to stop it but has the presence of mind to duck as he understands that the batsmen are going for the single. Bairstow quickly gets across and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Head was well in.
A short ball, outside off, Cummins sways away.
Beaten! Gets this one to land on the rough and beat the outside edge of the left-hander. Kept slightly low as well. Bairstow removed the bails but Head never went out.
Good length on middle and kept slightly low. Head did well to block.
Fuller on off again as Head lunges to block.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Another fullish ball on off, Head leans into the shot and drives this beautifully. The ball races through mid off for a boundary.
Fuller ball on off, Head blocks it off his front foot.
Pat Cummins walks out now. Counting the balls, are both the teams...

OUT! Caught! Is that a bird? Is that a plane? Is that Superman? No! It is Joe Denly. Take a bow. Plenty of drama left in this game. England 4 wickets away from levelling the series now. A short ball, outside off, Paine looks to pull but Joe Denly at square leg throws himself to his left, sticks out his hand and voila! It sticks! The entire English team is mobbing Denly who has probably made one of the biggest contributions of the match. That is a tough catch at this time of the night. Or evening, shall we say. Paine walks back shaking his head. 42 balls left. 4 wickets needed for England. 1-1 coming?
Outside off, very full, good thinking from Jofra, Tim drives it towards cover.
Another short ball, this is around his nose, the skipper rises and fends it down in front of short leg.

FOUR BYES! Too high for everyone. A short ball, around off, Paine leaps with the bounce and the ball goes well over him and his counterpart behind. Bairstow leaps but to no avail. The ball races to the fine leg fence.
Down the leg side, tickled towards fine leg for a single.
Full and around middle, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Another attempt to land it on the rough but no success as Paine blunts this with his pad.
Leach is aiming for the rough but unable to land it there. Paine pads it.
FOUR! SHOT! Fuller ball on the leg stump, the Aussie skipper slams this through the mid on region to get off the mark as the ball races to the fence.
Good length on middle, Head works it towards square leg to get a run.
Good length on middle, Head blocks it off his back foot.
Fuller on off, Head works it towards point with a push.
Around middle, played in front of short leg where Buttler collects and flicks it back at the stumps, hitting them down. Bairstow appeals for a run out but Paine never left his crease.
A bouncer now, TP ducks.
Around off, the skipper looks to tuck but misses and is hit on the stomach.
That has come in a long way! A length ball outside off, Tim looks to defend but the ball comes in a long way and cuts him into half, just going between bat and pad!
A ripper of a bouncer. Right at the body, Paine leaps to fend it off but gets hit on the arm. Paine does not show any pain, nor does he flinch.
On a length outside off, coming in, pushed towards backward point for a single. 59 balls left.
Tossed up outside off, solidly blocked towards the spinner. A wicket maiden for the left-arm spinner!
Full and around off, pushed back to Jack the bowler.
Lunges to defend and thrusts this off the splice, just short of Rory Burns at silly point!
Around off, punched back to Leach again.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler. No hat-trick!

OUT! CAUGHT! England are sensing a win now as Wade is outta here. Good length ball on middle, Wade comes forward to block this but the ball rises a tad bit to hit the gloves of Wade and lob towards the short leg fielder. Buttler is there and he is not going to drop that one. Leach doing a brilliant job here for the hosts.

Tim Paine walks in at number 7, replacing Wade. The door has been kicked wide open. England need 5 wickets. 65 balls remaining. Leach is on a hat-trick as well! Men everywhere. 4 men around the wicket plus the keeper.
Shortish one this time, Wade works it towards mid-wicket to keep strike.
Goes for a yorker for a change. But this went down the leg side as Wade missed his flick. A mild appeal from Bairstow there but nothing from others.
And again. Archer continues sending the bouncers. Another superb bouncer but Wade does well this time to duck.
The physio is out in the middle to check on Wade. Just having a look at the helmet. The norm these days.
FOUR LEG BYES! Where did that come from? Another bumper from Archer, aiming the head. Wade ducks at it but is hit on the helmet and the ball goes over the keeper for a boundary.
Goes for another bumper but this is on the leg side as Head works it fine to get a run.
Shortish length ball on off and middle, it didn't bounce much. Blocked well by Wade.
The match livens up again. 72 balls left. 6 wickets needed. Matthew Wade comes out to bat.

OUT! The decision is given as caught but Labuschagne does not agree. There are words exchanged between him and Joe Root but the latter says that he caught it. Anyways, it is an unlucky dismissal for the Ashes debutant. Full and around middle, Labuschagne looks to play the sweep but he hits it right into the left thigh of Jos Buttler at short leg. The ball lobs towards short mid-wicket where Joe Root dives forward and takes a stunner. England celebrate but Labuschagne is going nowhere. The two umpires have a chat and then refer it to their mate upstairs, with the soft signal as OUT. Here come the replays. From one angle looks like the ball has bounced. From another angle, it looks like the ball has gone into the hands. After a lot of checking, Wilson gives the decision as OUT. Labuschagne shakes his head and mutters some words to Root who says that he caught it cleanly. A sad way to go for the man who played so well. Coach Justin Langer will be remembering something. Flashback to Mumbai 2001. Batsman - Sachin Tendulkar. Bowler - Mark Waugh. Sachin pulls. Ball hits Langer at short leg. Ricochets to short mid-wicket where a certain Ricky Thomas Ponting dives to his right to take the catch. Both the men would be in the Aussie dressing room at the moment. Can comfort the youngster. End of a magnificent 85-run stand.

Labuschagne is caught! The umpires want to check that though for legality. The soft signal is OUT. Here come the replays. Has Joe Root taken that cleanly? Has the ball bounced before? From one angle, it seems like the ball has bounced. From another, it looks like it is clean. Third umpire Joel Wilson feels it is a wicket.
Bowls one down the leg side. Marnus lets it go.
Reverse sweep this time. This on middle and leg from Leach who is looking to land the ball on the rough. Marnus brings the reverse sweep through point to take a couple.
Again comes down the track to this fullish ball outside off and drives it through cover to pick a couple this time. Didn't go hard at the ball.
Blocked off the front foot this time by ML.
FOUR! Top Shot! Fullish ball on off, Marnus comes down the track to drive it superbly through covers to get another boundary.
Bowled the last one round the wicket looking for a shortish one but it is wide outside off, Head looks to go after the ball but he misses it.
Pushed towards square leg to get off strike.
That came in from outside off form a good length as ML left it alone.
This is another shortish one from Archer but this is on off, blocked nicely again by Marnus.
Shortish one on middle and leg, ML blocks it off his back foot.
Looks for a slower yorker first up but sends a full toss, Marnus reads it early to block.
Jofra Archer is back for a final burst. 10-2-26-2 so far. He might well bowl 7 on the trot here.
Comes down the track and drives it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Landed outside off, Head goes back and defends.

50 up for Marnus Labuschagne! He is playing as a like-for-like substitute for Smith and is playing a gutsy knock just like Smith. Full on off from Leach, Marnus pushes it towards mid off to take a run and get to his second half century. Good innings this from him.
Fullish one on middle, blocks it well.

FOUR! Good sweep shot! Looking for the rough around the leg side, Leach dishes a full toss on the legs of Marnus who sweeps it well through square leg to get another boundary. One away from his half century.

DRINKS BREAK. So Root is indeed taking the final hour. England have thrown everything that they had at Australia but Labuschagne and Head have played superbly. Guess Joe wants to give Jofra one final spell. If the hosts manage to pick up a wicket or two quickly, victory might still be in their grasp. The conditions have become bright and sunny, so if Joe Root wants to bowl all the 15 overs, he might be able to do it.
Around off, blocked back to the bowler.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
FOUR! Short and outside off. Easy pickings. Cut through the covers.

Short and outside off, Labuschagne pushes this through point. The ball runs away and Jack Leach runs behind it in circles. Fumbles but manages to recover the ball before it touches the ropes. Three runs taken.

Joe Root brings himself on. After this over, he has a decision to make. Either shake hands with the batsmen and call this game off. Or take the final hour and bowl the remaining 15 overs, whichever comes later.
That's hit the batsman on his pads.
That kept low! Fuller one on middle from Leach. Head is watching the ball well as he blocks it.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Head blocks it off his back foot.
Fuller ball on off and middle, Head taps it towards gully.
Good length one on middle, ML works it towards the leg side to take a run.
Middle and leg this time on a fullish length, Marnus pushes this towards the leg side.
Fuller outside off, Head leans to drive this straight to cover. Maiden over from Stokes but Head was confident too in this over.
Bumper outside off this time, no way Head is going to do anything on that.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, Head works it towards the leg side nicely.
Fullish one on middle this time, Head pushes it towards mid off.
Fifth stump line outside off, Head covers his stumps and lets it go.
Good length outside off, Head lets it go to the keeper.
Another sweep shot attempted, again a miss, this time there is no appeal.
LBW appeal, turned down. Pitched outside leg. ML looked to sweep but missed and was hit on the pads.
Pitched outside leg, Marnus looks to defend but the ball rips past the outside edge!
FOUR! Full and around middle, Labuschagne gets down and sweeps it through mid-wicket! Root now moves a man to deep mid-wicket for that slog sweep.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Works this through mid-wicket for a couple.
Oopsss... a high full toss, around leg, Travis spots it late and flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Much better. Full and outside off, Head leans and drives it through the covers.
The batsman was beaten and missed the line of the delivery.

FOUR! A misfield now. 'Can't catch, can't field,' quips Michael Holding on air. Full and outside off, Head leans and drives it towards point. Joe Denly gets across from backward point and slides but the ball goes through. The boundary brings a 50-run stand between the two.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

EDGED, DROPPED! Well, Australia put down a few while bowling, now it is England's turn. Full and outside off, Head looks to drive but gets a thick, fat outside edge. Straight into the bread basket of Jason Roy at second slip who puts it down! He seems to indicate that he could not quite sight the ball.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, ML pushes it towards the cover region where the fielder dives to stop the ball.
Good length on off, Marnus blocks it onto the pitch.
Beaten! Good delivery that. Went slightly away from Marnus as he looked to push it towards the off side but is beaten.
Shortish one on middle, Marnus goes back and looks to cut but finds the fielder.
Starts with a fuller ball on middle, Marnus pushes it towards mid on.
Spin again! Leach will look to use the rough.
FOUR! Outside off, Head reaches out and looks to drive but gets a bit of an outside edge which squirts away behind point.
Ohhh... gone. Plumb LBW. But... for the inside edge. Full and straight, Head looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. Stokes starts to appeal but then bails out on hearing the sound of wood.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
A bit of a delay. Stokes is switching angle and coming from around the wicket. Head is waiting for the sightscreen to get moved. Also, a window is open somewhere and he has that closed.
Outside off, left alone. 129 balls left.
Around off, blocked solidly.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Head punches this through cover-point and gets a boundary!
Ben Stokes to bowl now. 22 overs left in the day.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
FOUR! Neatly done. Full and outside off, Labuschagne steers this behind point for a boundary!
Outside off, solidly defended towards cover.
Walks across his stumps, exposing his leg stump and shoulders arms. That is the first time ML has done that. Perhaps Woakes can gamble by going down the leg side.

This one stays low! A length ball outside off, Marnus looks to defend but gets squared up as the ball shoots low. Very lucky that the bat came down just in time to sneak an outside edge. Off it went along the ground to second slip.

NOT OUT. Impact is outside. Good length ball on off, went slightly away from the right-hander Marnus' push towards the leg side to hit him on the pads. England players appeal but Aleem Dar says no. That looked a bit high to the naked eye but Root signals for a review very quickly. Interestingly, Woakes suggests him that it was high as well. No consultation there from the bowler it seemed. Ball Tracker arrives and it confirms the impact was outside off.

Root reviews one! May not be a bad call. Labuschagne has been hit in front but has been adjudged not out. Woakes feels it might be a bit high. Here comes Ball Tracker. Impact is outside off. Review lost by England but they may not mind it too much.
Shortish one on off and middle, Head blocks it onto the pitch.

Is this the first time in this whole match? England are trying desperately to get the ball changed. Chris Woakes shows it to umpire Chris Gaffaney who passes it through the 8-shaped gauge and then tosses it back to the bowler. Woakes smiles. At Edgbaston, both teams were aiming to change the ball frequently. But unsuccessfully.
Good length ball outside off, Head times it sweetly but finds the cover fielder.
FOUR! Poor ball! Dishes a fuller ball on the pads of Head this time. Head places it fine down the leg side to get his third boundary.
Good length ball on middle and off, Head comes forward and blunts this towards the leg side.
This time goes fuller on middle, Head works it straight to the fielder on the leg side.
Fullish length close to the off pole, Head blocks it towards cover.
Shortish one outside off this time, Head gets behind the line of the ball to tap it towards cover and take a run.
Full on middle this time as Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket to take a run.
Shortish on middle and leg from Broad, Marnus blunts it nicely towards the leg side off his back foot.

Good length outside off on the fourth stump line, Head looked to leave that one but was late in doing so. The ball took the outside edge and went towards Jason Roy in the slip cordon who couldn't stop it cleanly and the batters change ends. Awkward shot that.
Shortish one on middle and leg this time, Head works it towards the leg side off his back foot.
Shortish ball to start with but the line is not right. Goes down the leg side as Head misses his flick.
Change from both the ends as Woakes is on. Also, lights are on. There is some rain coming in from the south-west. Hopefully, it misses us.
A length ball, around off, tucked towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, let through to Bairstow.
FOUR! MARVELLOUS! Overpitched wide outside off, Labuschagne leans and drives it through cover-point!
Full and outside off, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
A length ball outside off, Marnus shoulders arms.
Good length outside off to start with, Labuschagne lets this go to the keeper.

Broad time as Archer gets some rest. One guesses it will be a while before Jofra returns. Root is lucky that he can throw the ball to a person who can give you wickets at this time of the day. Who better than Broad to finish this Aussie batting off? Michael Atherton reckons that it is 7 times that Broad has taken a 5-fer in a single spell. Yes. Single spell. 60 all out fresh in memory? An 8th 5-fer might do well here.
Oohhh... that was almost similar to the grubber which got Bancroft. Head smiles. Landed outside off, Travis looks to defend but just about gets his bat down in time to block.
Gets well outside the line of off and looks to sweep but misses and is hit on the pads.
Full again, outside off, Head looks to drive but mistimes it towards mid off.
Landed closer to the rough outside off, Travis lunges and dead-bats it. 159 balls left.
FOUR! MAJESTIC! Leach should not mind that. Tossed up outside off, just in front of the rough, Head leans and drives it through the covers.
Full and outside off, pushed past silly point towards cover.

Appeal from England but hardly anything from Jofra. Fullish ball on middle and leg to Head who looks to flick but is hit on the pads. The ball goes towards fine leg and the batters take a run. That looked going down and that's why no enthusiasm from Archer.
Shortish one this time, Head works it off his back foot.
Good length on middle and leg from Archer this time. It came in to Head who looks to work it towards the leg side but the ball hits the outer half of the bat and goes to point.
FOUR! Good length ball on middle and leg. Too easy for Head as he flicks this nicely through mid-wicket to get off the mark with a boundary.
Archer bangs this one from round the wicket looking to hit the ribs of the right-hander. The batter works it well off his back foot to take a run.
Shortish ball on fourth stump line, Marnus looks to slice this over the slip cordon but misses to get bat on ball. A risky attempt that.
Good length ball on middle, Labuschagne works it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Full one outside off, Marnus blocks it by coming forward.
Shortish one on off, Marnus times it well towards cover but finds the fielder.
Good length outside off, ML dabs the ball easily.
Another fuller one but Marnus leans into the shot to push it towards cover.
Looks for a fuller ball but dishes out a full toss on middle, Marnus blocks it back to the bowler.
Shortish ball on off and middle, this also came in to the left-hander who pushed towards the leg side awkwardly.
Short one outside off this time, Head lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish length on middle this time, Marnus flicks it nicely towards mid-wicket to get three. The deep square leg fielder hares at the ball to stop it.

Another one on good length on middle, this nips back in slightly to the right-hander and rises a bit as well. The batsman looks to tap it towards the leg side but the short leg fielder does well to stop it.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Marnus stands tall to tap this onto the pitch.
On a length around off, Labuschagne defends it solidly towards mid-wicket.
Landed outside off, Head gets a good stride forward and defends.
Full and around off, pushed towards long on for a single.
Down the leg side, tucked towards fine leg.
Pitched outside leg, on a fuller length, lands on the rough, spinning away. Marnus looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge which lands in front of second slip.
Lunges to this one and blocks it in front of short leg.
Full and outside leg, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball spins in, takes the inside edge and goes past short leg towards square leg.

MIX-UP, RUN OUT CHANCE, MISSED! FOUR OVERTHROWS! Everything happening. Shortish length on off from Archer, coming into the batsman. Labuschagne looks to work it towards the leg side but he is hit on the stomach. The ball rolls towards the slip cordon. Now, Marnus is busy recovering from the blow but Head meanwhile calls him for the single. Rory Burns gets to the ball from gully and has a shy at the non striker's end but misses. Had he hit, ML was a goner. He was a yard short. Stuart Broad was backing up from mid on but he has no chance. The ball races away to the long on fence.
Good length on off, ML blocks it awkwardly towards point.
Another bumper attempted but the line is outside off and Labuschagne is not interested. The ball shapes further away as Bairstow collects it close to first slip.
Shortish one outside off, Marnus lets that go.
Beaten this time! Good length ball outside off, in the channel for Marnus. He fends at it but the ball shapes a tad bit away to go past the batsman.
Good length ball on off and middle, ML taps it nicely off his back foot.
Again. This time played a bit better, off the face of the bat, towards backward point.
Oohhh... outside off, stays low, TH stays back to defend and gets a bit of the outer half of the bat towards point.

FOUR BYES! What was Travis doing there? His head is all over the place. Full and outside off, Head looks to sweep but at the last moment, he realizes that it is too full to be played. He looks to then guide it towards point but misses. The ball spins in, beats the bat and the keeper and races to the fence behind. 50 UP FOR AUSTRALIA. Runs do not matter. 194 balls left to negotiate.
Around off, spinning in, defended back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, tucked towards leg slip.
Full and outside off, Head looks to sweep but misses. The ball stays low and Bairstow does well to collect.
Good length ball on off, Marnus blocks it off the outer half of the bat.
Around off, Labuschagne looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and wears it on his thigh pads.
Good bouncer again. That came in from off. Marnus does well to sway away.
Fullish ball outside off, Marnus leans forward to drive it through covers and take a couple. Woakes chases the ball and returns it to the keeper.
A bouncer outside off, Labuschagne drops his wrists and allows the ball to go through past his face.
Full and outside off, watchfully pushed towards the bowler.
Travis Head is the next man for Australia. They are looking in a spot of bother here. Jofra Archer to continue from the other end for England.

OUT! LBW! That kept low. Never, never, never, play on the back foot to a spinner on the final day of a Test. You never know when one goes below. Bancroft will know now. Fullish ball on middle and leg from Leach, Cameron stays back to defend but misses. The ball stays low and hits him in front of the stumps. England appeal along with Leach and Aleem Dar has no hesitation in raising the finger. No way that is going to be reviewed. Absolutely plumb. A wicket in the first over after Tea for England.
Another fullish length  on off, Bancroft blocks it coming forward.
Good length ball on off, Bancroft pushes this towards cover.
Fuller on middle to Bancroft, he tucks it towards the leg side.
Leach is aiming the rough as he pitches another one on the same line as the last ball. This time the batter works it towards square leg to get the first run of the session.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Marnus pads it away.
The English players are out in the field. Labuschagne and Bancroft walk to the middle now. Leach to start the proceedings for England. Labuschagne to face first up.
... Day 5, Session 3 ...

Coming to the visitors' batting, this phase reminds us of the 70s and 80s when West Indian bowlers used to terrorize the opposition batsmen. Australia need to find a way not only to survive but do so with dignity.
