Even if they do not get all out, losing more than 6 wickets would send a negative message and that is something they would want to avoid. Want to. But can they? Join us back at 5 pm local (1600 GMT) for the final stages of this riveting match.

Of course, England's bowling is not all about Jofra, is it? Broad and Woakes are terrific in their own right, while Jack Leach, in the solitary over that he bowled before the break, got some cobras to spit around. Australia will have their hands full.

There were doubts whether Joe Root declared a bit too late to give his bowlers enough time to bowl Australia out. Turns out that he is in a good shape to scare the visitors out of their wits and also level the series with the kind of bowling which has been exhibited in the 13 overs bowled.

Whoa, this Test is alive and kicking! 35 overs left and 8 wickets needed. Any doubts whether England can win this or not? Lot to do with the fiery Archer. Scary Archer. Pumped up Archer. We are going to have a frenetic final session for sure.
Defended off the back foot by Bancroft. TEA ON DAY 5! England need 8 more wickets to win.
The batsman picked that bouncer early and let it through to the keeper.

On a length, going down leg, Bancroft tries to flick this one but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. It lobs up and Stokes at leg gully catches it. England appeal mildly thinking some bat might be involved but nothing doing for the umpire.
Bancroft shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the backfoot.
Length ball just outside off, ML guides it down to third man and they take three.

Hit on the hand very hard. Archer is consistently bowling dangerous line and lengths and troubling the visitors. This was on a length just outside off, Marnus looks to block at it but gets hit on the glove and he writhes in pain.
Tossed up around middle and off, Leach sweeps it towards square leg and takes one.
Floated full and on off, ML blocks it out.
Full and floated this one, pitches on the rough and bounces way higher than expected. Marnus looks to flick it towards the leg side but misses.
Floated and full on middle, Marnus blocks it out.
Flat and on middle, blocked out off the back foot by Marnus.
Short and just on the off pole, pushed to the cover fielder.
Spinner on now. Jack Leach is into the attack. Feel it is to get one over done quickly so that Jofra can have one more burst before Tea.
Another shorter one, again Bancroft ducks and evades this delivery.
Bouncer! Bancroft ducks and lets that one through to JB.
Length ball on middle and off, Bancroft blocks it out off the back foot.
Bancroft has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Hit on the stomach. Length ball on middle and off, the ball this time comes back in and CB wasn't expecting it. He shoulders arms but the ball comes in and hits him on the stomach.
Bancroft gets squared up again similarly. Length ball outside off, it pitches and nips away. He tries to defend but does so inside the line and misses the ball.
Change of ends for Jofra Archer.
Lets the last ball through to the keeper. Good batting here by Marnus.
FOUR! Full on off and middle, Marnus gets onto the back foot and flicks it nonchalantly towards the mid-wicket fence.
Length ball on middle and off, Labuschagne blocks it out.
Outside off, Marnus lets it through again.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Awkward leave by Marnus here, the ball pitches just outside off and comes in. Labuschagne hops away and lets it go.
Chris Woakes is into the attack for the hosts. He replaces Archer who was doing very well and also took both the wickets of this innings.
Fuller this time on off pole, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off again, CB shoulders arms to this one too.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.

Close again but just over short leg. Broad pitches this one outside off and gets it to nip back in off the surface. Bancroft looks to block it out but gets an inside edge on it and the ball then goes onto hit the thigh pad. It lobs over short leg and the ball goes towards square leg as they take a couple.
Again on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball just outside off, CB gets the outside half of his bat and the ball goes straight to the point fielder.

EDGED AND FOUR! Archer once again hits the deck hard on off, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes through the vacant gully region for a boundary. End of another entertaining and scary Jofra over.
Another beauty! Good length ball outside off, it zips away. Labuschagne looks to defend but once again gets squared up.

Excellent bowling. Archer steams in and once again bends his back on this one. The way he has bowled short balls has been impressive. This one is also right in the money, close to the body. Marnus does really well to sway away from it.
Outside off and pacy, Marnus looks to defend but the ball fizzes past him.
FOUR! This should give Marnus Labuschagne some much-needed confidence. Fuller on off, Labuschagne gets on his front foot and drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Labuschagne looks to defend but misses.

UPPISH AND JUST WIDE FOR FOUR! Agonizingly wide of the flying leg gully.  They kept a leg gully in place as Bancroft is playing a lot of uppish flicks but they moved Stokes a bit wide as they expected him to flick it there. However, Cameron flicks it fine this time, just inches away to the right of the diving Ben Stokes. Had Ben stayed at his original position, Bancroft was a goner.
Length ball on middle, Labushagne flicks it towards square leg and gets off the mark.

Very good take from  Bairstow. Broad strays his line and bowls one down the leg side, Marnus looks to flick but misses. The ball keeps going down, Bairstow dives to his left and stretches to save a certain 4 leg byes.
Full with very little movement on this one outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Uppish but safe. Good length ball on top of middle and leg, Bancroft shuffles across and glances it uppishly towards the square leg region for a single.
Fuller around off, Bancroft gets on his front foot and drives it crisply through covers for a couple.
Again squared up by Archer! The batsman was beaten and missed the line of the delivery.
Beaten! Jofra follows the short ball up with a length ball outside off, Labuschagne goes for the defense but is squared up. Oohs and Aahs all around the ground.

Concussion test for the one who is substituting for the concussed? This is something new. Labuschagne is giving a thumbs up, showing that he is okay but the physio is out in the middle. A new helmet comes out for Marnus. Boy, are Australia already looking for the overs remaining in the day? All ready to go now.

Ouch! Again on the helmet and this time it is Marnus. Jofra hits the deck hard and the ball shoots up off the surface. It rapidly rises on Marnus who fails to duck in time. He is hit flush on his helmet and falls down but quickly gets up and says that he is fine.
Wide! Bouncer but way over the head of Labuschagne. Welcomed to the crease by Archer well.

Marnus Labuschagne is the new man in. He was not in the actual playing XI but has come into the side as a concussion substitute for Steve Smith, who has been the best batsman in this series. Big shoes to fill for Labuschagne.

OUT! Jofra takes his second and he is on fire here! Bowls this one on a length on the leg pole, the ball pitches and just drifts away from the southpaw. Khawaja looks to defend it but gets the faintest of outside edges on it. It carries to Jonny Bairstow behind the stumps and he completes the formalities. Now, Jofra barely appeals but someone does and umpire Aleem Dar raises his finger immediately. England are all smiles but Uzzie looks bemused. He is standing there, asking Bancroft something who comes running towards him. They chat about the review and Usman shakes his head to something. Surely, he must be knowing whether he nicked it or not? Now, he turns back and walks. Australia are 2 down (for now) before Tea.
Full on middle and off, Khawaja punches it down the ground towards long off and takes a couple.
Jofra bowls this one just outside off, Khawaja goes for the defense but it is squared up.
FOUR! On the pads of Bancroft and he just flicks it away towards mid-wicket nonchalantly for a boundary.
Length ball just outside off, Bancroft tries to defend and gets a faint outside edge on it. It carries to first slip on a bounce.
CB chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Full and wide outside off, Broad lures Bancroft into the cover drive. He goes for it but misses the ball completely. Australia might be panicking here.
Good length ball on off, pushes this one towards mid off.
Length delivery on middle and off, Bancroft blocks it out.
Archer now comes steaming in and bowls a good length ball on off, Khawaja looks to defend but the ball hits him high on his bat and goes to point.
Now full on the pads, Usman flicks it but straight to mid-wicket.

Hostile welcome for Usman Khawaja. Archer has his tails up and there is no doubt about it. He steams in and bowls a pacy bouncer around off. Khawaja takes his eyes off the ball but it goes away to the keeper.
Usman Khawaja walks out at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT! Warner is out and Australia are one down as Jofra takes the first one. He pitches this one on middle and off on a length, the ball pitches and moves away from Warner. He goes with hard hands at it and gets a thick outside edge which carries to gully where Rory Burns was stationed and he takes it cleanly. Australia again lose Warner cheaply. Well, no Smith first itself. Now, Warner fails to stand up. Could be a tough evening for the Aussies.
Played through mid-wicket by Bancroft. They take a single.
Edged but falls short! Bancroft goes to push this one towards the off side but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball falls just short of the slip cordon.
Again full and on the pads, Bancroft pushes this one towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

On the pads of Warner, he flicks it towards backward square leg and takes a single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. However, the batter was well in and it wouldn't have made any difference.
Warner has a wild slash at this wide and short ball but misses it completely.
Length ball on middle and off, Warner blocks this one out.
Wide outside off, Warner shoulders arms to let that one through.
FOUR LEG BYES! Down the leg side, Warner looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the pads. It flicks his pads and goes towards the fine leg boundary.
Fuller this time, Cb defends this one off the front foot back to the bowler.
Outside off, the batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Bancroft has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Squared up completely! Jofra bowls this on a length outside off, it pitches and nips away. CB plays inside the line of the delivery and does not edge it.
No ball! Archer oversteps this time. Outside off, CB lets it through.

Bancroft survives! Length ball on off, swings a tad bit inside, Bancroft goes for the push but gets an inside edge on it and the ball hits his thigh pad. Cameron is a lucky man that the ball does not go onto chop the stumps.
Smooth run up and length delivery outside off, Bancroft lets it through.
Speedster, Jofra Archer to bowl from the other end.
Again angling in towards the southpaw, this time Warner gets an inside edge on this one and the ball rolls towards mid-wicket.
Wide outside off, Warner shoulders arms to it.
This time safely defended off the front foot by Warner.
